(5,'Ikseon-dong Hanok Village','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/IkseongdongHanokVillage/ENP037008','The Ikseon-dong Hanok Village spans a length of around 801 m, connecting Ibis Ambassador, Insadong, and Nakwon Sanga, or Nakwon Music Market, and is home to all kinds of fusion-concept cafes, restaurants, and shops that contrast with the more traditional vibe of the neighboring Insadong area. In fact, it\'s one of the most popular sights for dating in the city! Despite the relatively narrow alleyways of the village, you are in for a treat during the winter season or night hours with the quaint, yet striking scenery all around.      Frequently Asked Questions about Ikseon-dong Hanok Village        What is the nearest subway station to Ikseon-dong Hanok Street?         The nearest subway station to Ikseon-dong Hanok Street is Jongno 3-ga Station (Subway Line 1, 3, 5).          Are there any tourist attractions worth visiting near Ikseon-dong Hanok Street?         These are the following tourist attractions around Ikseon-dong Hanok Street.     Jongmyo Shrine     Gwanghwamun Square     Gyeongbokgung Palace        { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"FAQPage\", \"mainEntity\": [{ \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"What is the nearest subway station to Ikseon-dong Hanok Street?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div>The nearest subway station to Ikseon-dong Hanok Street is Jongno 3-ga Station (Subway Line 1, 3, 5).</div>\" } }, { \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Are there any tourist attractions worth visiting near Ikseon-dong Hanok Street?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div> These are the following tourist attractions around Ikseon-dong Hanok Street.<br><br> <ul> <li><a href=\\\"https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Jongmyo_/549\\\"style=\\\"color:#0000EE;text-decoration: underline\\\">Jongmyo Shrine</a></li> <li><a href=\\\"https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Gwanghwamun-Square_/1901\\\"style=\\\"color:#0000EE;text-decoration: underline\\\">Gwanghwamun Square</a></li> <li><a href=\\\"https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Gyeongbokgung-Palace_/73\\\"style=\\\"color:#0000EE;text-decoration: underline\\\">Gyeongbokgung Palace</a></li> </ul> </div>\" } }, { \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"Ikseon-dong Hanok Village\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.5\", \"ratingCount\": \"72\" }, \"review\": { \"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": { \"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\" }, \"author\": { \"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Yi Qin\" }, \"reviewBody\": \"Recommended by a local to visit which turns out to be one of the most memorable moment of our trip. The area is made up of connecting alleys which makes you feel like you are in a maze but there\'s something good waiting for you at every turn. Quaint little shops and cafes converted from ancient architectures filled up the streets, displaying a perfect blend of modern and history in the heart of Seoul.\", \"datePublished\": \"2020-03-15\" } }] }','','','','03133  17, Donhwamun-ro 11ga-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 1 / 3 / 5, Jongno 3-ga Station, Exit 4,  141m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67734&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67735&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67736&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67737&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67738&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.573390,'ENP037008'),
(6,'Night Views at Banpodaegyo Bridge','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Night-Views-at-Banpodaegyo-Bridge/ENP016325','Banpodaegyo Bridge is a two level bridge that crosses the Hangang River. The Moonlight Rainbow Fountain display takes place at this bridge and it\'s often possible to see fireworks here as well. The area is a popular date spot and the view at night is beautiful. Bask in the atmosphere and the views of the Hangang River at Banpodaegyo Bridge.','-4278','','','2085-14, Olympic-daero, Seocho-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 3/7/9  Express Bus Terminal Station  Exit 8-1,  850m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42326&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42327&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12910&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12909&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.511983,'ENP016325'),
(7,'ParkNoSoo Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/ParkNoSoo-Museum/ENP042350','Pro-Japanesepolitician Yoon Deok-young built the house for his daughter in 1937, whichlater became painter Park No-soo??s house in 1973. Park No-soo, who devotedhimself to art over the 40 years he lived in this house, donated it back tosociety along with his artwork. The historical residence was reborn as an artmuseum in 2013 through the Jongno Cultural Foundation.  Despiteits long history of 80 years, this well-maintained building was recognized forits cultural value and was registered Cultural Heritage Material No. 1 of Seoulin 1991.','-6239','Daily 10:00 ~ 18:00','Closed Mondays','03034  34, Ogin 1-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Gyeongbokgung Station  Exit 2,  870m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56153&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56154&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56155&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56156&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56157&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.581367,'ENP042350'),
(8,'Sungkyunkwan University','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Sungkyunkwan-University/ENP019656','Sungkyunkwan University was founded in 1398 and it is the oldest university in Asia. The university was founded by the first king of the Joseon Dynasty, King Taejo of Joseon. Sungkyunkwan University has two campuses, one located in Seoul and the other in the city of Suwon. The Seoul campus is located near Hyehwa Station and visitors can see historical buildings that date back to the Joseon era.','-794','','','03063  25-2, Sungkyunkwan-ro (Sungkyunkwan Univ.), Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Hyehwa Station  Exit 4,  1.2km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=13223&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=13224&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=13225&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73926&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73927&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.588227,'ENP019656'),
(9,'Namsan Cable Car','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Namsan-Cable-Car/ENP035015','The Namsan Cable Car is the most convenient and fun way to reach the summit of Namsan Mountain! In just a three-minute ride, you can reach the mountain peak up near the N Seoul Tower all the while enjoying a fantastic overlook of downtown Seoul. Not only can you experience the breathtaking view of the autumn foliage in the fall and snow-covered mountainside in the winter, but you can even catch a gorgeous aerial view of the city at night. Near the parking lot of the cable car, the surrounding neighborhood has a great selection of popular restaurants offering tasty menu items from tonkatsu (breaded pork cutlet) to vegetarian bibimbap and more! The 140-meter long Namsan outdoor elevator, Namsam Ormi, is also available for easy access to the cable car platform!','-3076','Daily 10:00 - 23:00 KST','','04630  83, Sopa-ro, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Myeongdong Station  Exit 4,  571m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=32472&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=32473&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=32475&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.557733,'ENP035015'),
(10,'Bugak Skyway Octagonal Pavilion','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/BugakSkywayPavilion/ENP011117','Bugak Skyway, which runs along the northeast ridge of Bugaksan (Mt.), has become known as the most beautiful driving route in Korea ever since it opened in September of 1968. The road is forested by thick greenery and leads to an octagonal pavilion (Palgakjeong) located at the top of the mountain, allowing visitors to appreciate a panoramic view of the whole city of Seoul. Ever since Palgakjeong and the surrounding areas underwent renovation and re-opened in April 2010, Bugak Skyway has grown to become a must for local residents and tourists alike. Palgakjeong is located at an elevation of 342 m, allowing visitors to appreciate not only the beauty of mother nature but also a panoramic view of the entire city. Visitors can enjoy a traditional plaza, a pagoda resting area, a wildflower garden and walking trails.        Frequently Asked Questions about Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong Pavilion         What are Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong Pavilion\'s operating hours?         Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong Pavilion is open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. (As of 2025)          I am curious about the location and price of the Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong Pavilion parking lot.         Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong parking lot is next to Bugak Palgakjeong Pavilion (San 6-18, Pyeongchang-dong, Jongno-gu, Seoul). The parking fee is 400 KRW per 10 minutes. (As of 2025)     { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"FAQPage\", \"mainEntity\": [{ \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"What are Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong Pavilion\'s operating hours?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div>Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong Pavilion is open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. (As of 2024)</div>\" } }, { \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"I am curious about the location and price of the Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong Pavilion parking lot.\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div>Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong parking lot is next to Bugak Palgakjeong Pavilion (San 6-18, Pyeongchang-dong, Jongno-gu, Seoul). The parking fee is 400 KRW per 10 minutes. (As of 2024)</div>\" } }, { \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"Bugak Skyway Palgakjeong Pavilio\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4\", \"ratingCount\": \"13\" }, \"review\": { \"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": { \"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\" }, \"author\": { \"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Philip P\" }, \"reviewBody\": \"De pavilion itself is not very particular, but the views from that mountain are stunning! Walk through the park, look in all directions. Not to be missed!\", \"datePublished\": \"2022-04-29\" } }] }','','','','03010  267, Bugaksan-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Hansung University Station  Exit 6,  take bus 1112 or 1111, get off at Seoul Dawon School or Han Yong-un Activity Center, 2.3 km.','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68348&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68349&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68350&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68351&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68352&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.606902,'ENP011117'),
(11,'Digital Media City','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Digital-Media-City/ENP011142','Digital Media City (DMC) is an IT and media industry cluster located in Mapo-gu, housing numerous headquarters of major domestic corporations. Currently, it hosts the three major terrestrial broadcasters KBS, MBC, and SBS, along with cable channels like YTN, Channel A, and JTBC, and newspapers such as Dong-A Ilbo and JoongAng Ilbo. Additionally, the Korean Film Archive, the nation\'s only film archive equipped with Korean movie films and related materials, is located there. This makes DMC a hub for the production of Hallyu content. Furthermore, the area is surrounded by various renowned restaurants, making it a recommended tourist destination for those interested in K-media.   { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"Digital Media City\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.0\", \"ratingCount\": \"12\" }, \"review\": [{ \"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": { \"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\" }, \"author\": { \"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"JHL\" }, \"reviewBody\": \"This area is the complex of broadcast centers. While walking on broad roads you can watch various art works frequently seen on TV news.With restaurants and cafés, it\'s not a bad place for a half day trip. Also, World Cup Park which is a huge park area including the famous Haneul Park is close.\", \"datePublished\": \"2020-05-29\" }] }','','','','366, World Cup buk-ro, Mapo-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 6/Gyeongui-Jungang Line/Airport Railroad, Digital Media City Station, Exit 9, 520','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=18018&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=18019&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=18020&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=18021&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.577731,'ENP011142'),
(12,'Banpodaegyo Bridge Moonlight Rainbow Fountain','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Banpodaegyo-Bridge-Moonlight-Rainbow-Fountain/ENP002220','Banpodaegyo Bridge is a two-tiered bridge over the Han River that features the Moonlight Rainbow Fountain, (the world??s longest bridge fountain recognized by the Guinness Book of World Records) with 380 water jets and a dazzling array of multi-colored lights. The Moonlight Rainbow Fountain??s water jets are dynamic and can move in time to music creating spectacular ever-changing displays. Add to that the hundreds of rainbow-colored lighting combinations when night falls, and it is easy to see why Banpodaegyo Bridge is a magnet for tourists year round.   The Moonlight Rainbow Fountain operates from April to October every year, however the schedule of the fountain shows varies from month to month. Each fountain show lasts 20 minutes. In addition, Banpo Hangang Park hosts the \"Moonlight Square Cultural Weekend\" event every Saturday from 7:00 - 8:30 p.m. from May to October, featuring a variety of musical styles including classical music with commentary, acappella, popera, jazz, brass bands and orchestras.    Frequently Asked Questions about Banpo Bridge Rainbow Fountain         What are Banpo Bridge Rainbow Fountain\'s operating hours?         The Banpo Bridge Rainbow Fountain operates in an increment of 20 minutes, and the operating hours are as follows. (As of 2024)     ??Low season (April-June, September-October): 12:00, 19:30, 20:00, 20:30, 21:00   ??Peak season (July-August): 12:00, 19:30, 20:00, 20:30, 21:00, 21:30   ??Fountain operation may be suspended depending on weather conditions (rain, strong wind) and the number of visitors in the park. (Fountain shutdown conditions: When predicting precipitation during the fountain\'s operating hours (??In the case of a clear day after rain, the facility will be inspected and operated when there are no abnormalities (to prevent malfunction due to humidity), when ther