(13,'Jahamun Tunnel','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Jahamun-Tunnel/ENP037158','Jahamun Tunnel is a tunnel connecting Cheongdong and Buam-dong in Seoul, and was featured as a filming site for the movie \"Parasite.\" In the movie, this is where Ki-taek and his family pass through in the pouring rain. This small scene has caused Jahamun Tunnel to attract countless tourists and movie fans.','','','','03022  219, Jahamun-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul, Korea (Buam-dong)','Subway Line 3 Gyeongbokgung Station Exit 3, take bus number 1020, 7022, or 7212, and get off at Buam Community Center,  650m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40989&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40990&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40991&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75392&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75393&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.591147,'ENP037158'),
(14,'Seoullo 7017','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seoullo-7017/ENP023496','Seoullo 7017 is an elevated sky garden that is a popular walking destination and tourist spot in the center of Seoul. Originally a highway overpass, it has since been transformed into a pedestrian walkway for the general public to enjoy. Seoullo\'s name is a nod to its original foundation in 1970 and its rebirth in 2017 as a sky garden. There are also 17 pedestrian pathways that allow visitors to walk through several local communities. Seoullo 7017 offers several rest areas, greenery, and cultural experiences at 1 kilometer above street-level.','-7250','Open 24 hours','Open year round','04509  432, Cheongpa-ro, Jung-gu, Seoul   (Bongnae-dong 2-ga, KORAIL Seoul Headquarters)','Subway Line 1/4/Gyeongui-Jungang Line/AREX, Seoul Station  Exits Exit 7,  148m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42213&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=6&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42214&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42274&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42273&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=8&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42275&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.557674,'ENP023496'),
(15,'ChoiManLin Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/ChoiManLin-Museum/ENP042352','Theelegant two-story, Western-style building was built in the 1970s. Here,sculptor Choi Man Lin created his world of art for about 30 years from 1988. Evenwith all its traces of artistry intact, it eventually grew to become the ChoiMan Lin Museum with the help of the Seongbuk-gu District and EMA Architects. Reborn as an art museum in2019, this building contains the traces of sculptor Choi Man Lin, which werepreserved through a remodeling method that protects the appearance of theexisting building as much as possible. Thisbuilding, which shows off its architectural beauty while maximizing itsfunction as an art museum, won the Excellence Award at the 2020 Public BuildingAwards of Korea.','-11888','Daily 10:00 ~ 18:00\nClosed for exhibition preparation (July 1 - September 3)','Closed Sundays & Mondays','02708  23, Solsaem-ro 7-gil, Seongbuk-gu, Seoul','Subway Uisinseol   Bukhansanbogukmun Station Exit 2,  438m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56158&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56159&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56160&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56161&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56162&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.610674,'ENP042352'),
(16,'Myeongdong Jaemi-ro','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/2024-jaemiro/ENPhvgb2b','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}Jaemi-ro is a comic street located in Myeongdong, Jung-gu. It is a content-specialized street within Sangsang Town\'s cultural content clustering, centered around the former Seoul Animation Center (currently undergoing reconstruction). It\'s a themed street stretching approximately 450m from Exit 3 of Myeongdong Station to the former Seoul Animation Center, adorned with Korean comics, animations, characters, illustrations, and other content. Jaemi-ro, connecting the iconic tourist spots of Seoul, Myeongdong, and Namsan Mountain, offers a valuable experience where visitors can enjoy diverse cultural experiences within the heart of Seoul\'s downtown area.','','','','04631  24, Toegye-ro 20-gil, Jung-gu, Seoul, Republic of Korea','Subway Line 3  Myeongdong Station  Exit 3,  196m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=64814&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=64815&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=64816&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english