(27,'National Assembly Building','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/National-Assembly-Building/ENP005763','The National Assembly Building houses Korea\'s legislative branch of government and it is located in Yeouido. The building represents the democracy and human rights of Korea. The National Assembly Library is located to the right of the main building, and the Assembly Members??Office Building is located to the left. Free tours of the National Assembly are available, but reservations are required. Visitors must reserve a tour date at least three days in advance of the desired visit date.','-8822','Weekdays: 10:00 AM - 17:00 (Entry available at 10:00, 11:00, 14:00, 15:00, 16:00, and 17:00.; Maximum 150 people per session)  \nSaturdays: 10:00 - 12:00 (Entry available at 10:00, 11:00, and 12:00; Maximum 150 people per session)','Closed Sundays, holidays & May 31st','07233  1, Uisadang-daero, Yeongdeungpo-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 9  National Assembly Station  Exit 1,  438m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68371&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68372&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68373&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68374&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68375&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.531058,'ENP005763'),
(28,'Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP)','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Dongdaemun-Design-Plaza-en/ENP024679','The Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP), planned by Seoul City Hall in 2006, opened its doors on March 21, 2014. The purpose of DDP is to utilize design thinking for innovation and development. It also showcases global design trends and design innovation as a birthplace of creative knowledge in the 21st century. As a multi-purpose cultural space, Dongdaemun Design Plaza has been hosting various cultural events since its opening, including exhibitions, fashion shows, new product launches, forums, and conferences. Additionally, the seasonal Seoul Light event transforms DDP\'s exterior walls into a curved silver canvas, offering diverse scenery.        Frequently Asked Questions about Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP)         Who can access the Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP)?         The Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP) is a cultural complex open to all citizens. Not only designers but also students who study design and culture and ordinary citizens, anyone can access it.          Are there lockers at Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP)?         For storing items, you can use the paid lockers near Subway Exit 1, on the first floor of the Design Lab, and inside the Art Hall. (As of 2024, specific locations may change)          How much is parking at Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP)?         The parking fee at Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP) is 400 KRW per 5 minutes (4,800 KRW per hour), with a daily maximum of 50,000 KRW. (As of 2024)     { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"FAQPage\", \"mainEntity\": [{ \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Who can access the Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP)?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div>The Dongdaemun Design Plaza (DDP) is a cultural complex open to all citizens. Not only designers but also students who study design and culture and ordinary citizens, anyone can access it.</div>\" } }, { \"@type\