(31,'Herb Astronomy Park','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/HerbAstronomyPark/ENP037130','Iljasan Herb Astronomical Park, located in Dunchon-dong, Gangdong-gu, Seoul, is an intimate park that is popular for enjoying nature. There is an astronomical observatory that can be used 24 hours a day. Additionally, as the name may entail, there are fresh herbs that grow around the park making it a fragrant space where you can feel relaxed while walking or jogging along the well-maintained trails. After dark, you can see hundreds of tiny lights that illuminate the space, making it even more beautiful.','','','','134-060  86 Dunchon-dong, Gangdong-gu, Seoul, South Korea','Subway Line 9  VHS Medical Center Station  Exit 3,  Take the blue bus 342 or the green bus 2312 ??get off at the Gildong Natural Ecology Park,  296m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40385&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40386&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40384&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40383&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40381&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.530230,'ENP037130'),
(32,'N Seoul Tower at Night','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/NSeoulToweratNight/ENP016321','N Seoul Tower is one of Seoul\'s most famous landmarks and one of the city\'s most beloved attractions. The views from the tower are beautiful but the night views are especially breathtaking. Visitors can take in incredible panoramic views of Seoul from the tower\'s observatory. The tower has been used as a filming location in many Korean TV shows and movies. One of the tower\'s attractions is the locks of love that visitors fasten to Namsan\'s iron railings.      For more information:    N    Seoul Tower     Namsan Park','-12652','10:00-22:30','Open year round','04340  105, Namsangongwon-gil, Yongsan-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 3/4  Chungmuro Station or Subway Line 3  Dongguk University Station. Take Circular Bus No. 01 (Namsan Circular) ??get off at the \"Namsan Seoul Tower\" stop ??walk 357m (8-minute walk)\n\nTake the Seoul City Tour Bus ??get off at the \"N Seoul Tow','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=8809&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72914&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72915&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72916&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.548942,'ENP016321'),
(33,'Figure and Ground','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Figure-and-Ground/ENP042255','Figure and Ground is dressed in red brick, a material commonly used in architecture, but the exterior is wrapped in thin strips going around the building that exudes intense sophistication. It is even more meaningful in that it is a reconstruction of the original form of the 30-something-year-old building that once stood in its place. With a cafe and a boutique on the lower floors and a shared office on the upper floors coexisting in one building, Figure and Ground is buzzing on weekdays and weekends, day and night.','','Ground level café, Conflict Store : Daily 10:00 ~ 22:00','','06036  53, Nonhyeon-ro 153-gil, Gangnam-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3/Shinbundang Line  Sinsa Station  Exit 8,  541m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=55789&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=55790&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=55791&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=55792&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=55793&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.520162,'ENP042255'),
(34,'Gwanghwamun Square','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Gwanghwamun-Square/ENP001899','King Taejo of the Joseon Dynasty moved the capital to Hanyang in 1394 and built Gyeongbokgung Palace, the official residence of the Joseon Dynasty. In addition, on both sides of the road in front of the palace??s main gate, the Street of Six Ministries, including Uijeongbu (State Council), was built. It was the best road in Hanyang. In 2009, that road opened again. Gwanghwamun Square and Cheonggye Plaza were built. The square is mostly ??a square that restores the history of Gwanghwamun,????a square that recreates the scenery of the Street of the Six Ministries,????an emblematic square of Korea,????an urban culture square where citizens mingle,????a square in the city center,??and ??a connection to the Cheonggyecheon Stream.??It functions as a space for history, culture, and relaxation. The focal point of this emblematic square in Korea is the statue of King Sejong the Great. The ??downtown square??around the statue of Admiral Yi Sun-sin is also a space appreciated by city dwellers. In addition, artificial ponds and fountains are installed to cool off people from the summer heat. Also, the Haechi statue and Grass Plaza, which are symbols of Seoul, were also created.','-40','Open 24 hours a day, throughout the year, as a city square','Open year-around','03172  B 175, Sejong-daero, Jongno-gu, Seoul, Korea (??종??? ??종??야???','Subway Line 5  Gwanghwamun Station  Exit 2,  235m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=66716&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=66717&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=66718&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=66719&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.572236,'ENP001899'),
