(40,'Sebitseom (Sebitseom Island)','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Sebitseom/ENP024645','Sebitseom, also known as Sebit Islets, with the meaning ??three shining islands brightening the Hangang River??is the world??s first floating cultural space. It is made up of four artificial islands with wedding halls, Italian restaurants, buffets and cafes, exhibitions, performances and it is used as a marina for yachts and boats!    The Some Sevit, known to be a popular spot for nightlife in South Korea, has colorful and beautiful LED lights that reflect off of the Hangang River, making it a popular filming location for various dramas and movies, such Avengers: Age of Ultron. Enjoy delicious meals and cultural experiences, and remember to bring a camera for the various photo spots at the Floating Island Convention center, the outdoor deck and the roof observatory.','-4919','Daily 11:00 - 22:00','','06500  2085-14, Olympic-daero, Seocho-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 3/7/9, Express Bus Terminal Station, Exit 8-1,  650 m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42023&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42026&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42027&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73934&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73935&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.511983,'ENP024645'),
(41,'Hangang Eland Cruise','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Hangang-Cruise/ENP002126','The ultimate way to experience the Hangang River is by embarking on a cruise. Feel the refreshing breeze as you enjoy the picturesque views along both banks. Various cruises are available day and night, allowing you to appreciate the river??s beauty in a different light. The \"Hangang Tour Cruise\" runs daily during the day, offering a chance to explore Seoul\'s cityscape while enjoying live entertainment. Every evening at 6 PM, the \"Sunset Cruise\" provides a romantic view of the setting sun. For those who prefer evening or night outings, the \"Moonlight Music Cruise\" and \"Starlight Cruise\" offer stunning nighttime views of the Hangang River. Special options like the \"Fireworks Music Cruise,\" featuring dazzling displays, and the \"Dinner Cruise,\" which includes a buffet or champagne, add an extra luxury to your river experience.Aboard the cruise, you can enjoy live music while soaking in the sights of Seoul\'s iconic landmarks, including Sebitseom Island, Nodeul Island, Yeouido, the National Assembly Building, and Jamsil. It??s an ideal way to spend quality time with a partner, friends, or family, and offers a serene setting for those who wish to enjoy some peaceful reflection alone. Since schedules and routes vary by course, checking the official website for detailed information is advisable.','-13111','10:00 AM - 22:00 (Varies per course)\n- Duration may vary depending on the departure point and whether it\'s a round-trip or one-way route.  \n- For detailed schedule information, please refer to the website or call.','In case of natural disasters or severe weather conditions.','07337  Yeouido Dock: E-Land Cruise Ticket Office, 280 Yeouidong-ro, Yeongdeungpo-gu, Seoul / Jamsil Dock: Jamsil E-Cruise, 2 Baekjegobun-ro, Songpa-gu, Seoul','Yeouido Dock:  Subway Line 5  Yeouinaru Station  Exit 3,  613m  \nJamsil Dock:  Subway Line 2  Jamsilsaenae Station  Exit 6,  999m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=1318&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=1321&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=1322&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.524869,'ENP002126'),
(42,'Songwoldong','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Songwol-dong/ENP010567','Songwoldong is a neighborhood in northern Seoul that is home to many of the city\'s historic sites. Deoksugung Palace, the Seoul Museum of History, Gyeonghuigung Palace, Sungnyemun Gate, Seodaemun Prison History Hall and Dongnimmun Gate are all found in Songwoldong. Visitors to Seoul can experience Korean history through a visit to this beautiful and charming area. The area has also been used as a filming location for many Korean TV shows including \"Rooftop Prince.\" Songwoldong is easily accessible by car or public transportation.','-40','','','Songwol-dong, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 5  Seodaemun Station  Exit 3','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=5335&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=5336&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73948&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73949&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.570077,'ENP010567'),
(43,'Korea Central Mosque','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seoul-Central-Mosque/ENP004863','Located in Hannam-dong, Yongsan-gu, Seoul, the Seoul Central Mosque is the first Islamic Mosque in Korea. It was established on May 21, 1976, after construction began in October 1974. The Korean government provided the site in May 1969 with approximately 4,958 square meters of land, and the construction costs were supported by Islamic countries worldwide, including Saudi Arabia. Situated between the Hangang River and Namsan Mountain, the mosque features prayer halls on the first and second floors, with ablution rooms for men and women in the basement of the annex building. The first floor of the annex houses classrooms, while the second floor has office spaces. The adjacent Islamic Center includes facilities such as an Islamic mission center for children, a Muslim congregation, a women\'s association, and a library. The exterior of the Seoul Central Mosque features a variety of amenities, including halal restaurants, a halal butcher shop, an Islamic bookstore, a halal supermarket, and a travel agency, making it convenient for Muslims and non-Muslims to visit.       Frequently Asked Questions about Korea Central Mosque         What is the nearest subway station to the Seoul Central Mosque?         The nearest subway station to the Seoul Central Mosque is Itaewon Station (Subway Line 6).          Are there any precautions when visiting the Seoul Central Mosque?         You are not allowed to wear revealing clothing such as sleeveless tops, short skirts, or shorts, and smoke inside the mosque. If you enter the mosque wearing revealing clothing, you must put on appropriate attire (such as skirts and hijabs) available in the dressing room next to the security office. Non-Muslims are allowed to enter the mosque, but be careful not to interfere with the prayers by pointing the camera in front of people.          I am curious about the Seoul Central Mosque worship schedule.         You can check the Seoul Central Mosque monthly worship schedule on the website below.    Seoul Central Mosque Worship Schedule      { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"FAQPage\", \"mainEntity\": [{ \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"What is the nearest subway station to the Seoul Central Mosque?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div> The nearest subway station to the Seoul Central Mosque is Itaewon Station (Subway Line 6). </div>\" } }, { \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Are there any precautions when visiting the Seoul Central Mosque?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div> You are not allowed to wear revealing clothing such as sleeveless tops, short skirts, or shorts, and smoke inside the mosque. Non-Muslims are allowed to enter the mosque, but be careful not to interfere with the prayers by pointing the camera in front of people. </div>\" } }, { \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"I am curious about the Seoul Central Mosque worship schedule.\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div> You can check the Seoul Central Mosque monthly worship schedule on the website below.<br><br> <a href=\\\"http://www.koreaislam.org/en/prayer-times/\\\"style=\\\"color:#0000EE;text-decoration:underline\\\">Seoul Central Mosque Worship Schedule</a> </div>\" } }, { \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"the Seoul Central Mosque\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.5\", \"ratingCount\": \"125\" }, \"review\": { \"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": { \"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\" }, \"author\": { \"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"eddyphdhong\" }, \"reviewBody\": \"my the first time to visit here. only one mosque in korea i think. good place to visit. in itaewon area. with muslim friends it??s good time to show them here\", \"datePublished\": \"2020-02-08\" } }] }','-7621','Prayer services differ depending on time 