(55,'Yonghakgeong (Mokdong Archery Club)','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Yonghakgeong-Mokdong-Archery-Club/ENP002250','Yonghakgeong was once a military training ground, and is now known as the Mokdong Archery Club. The club has membership system but one-off lessons can be reserved in advance. After making a reservation, visitors can take archery lessons at the center. There is a pavilion, Western-style archery center (Yanggung Center) and Korean-style archery center (Gukgung Center). Visitors can choose from Western or Korean-style bows for their lessons.','-7484','Yanggung Center\'s Day Lessons: Tuesday & Wednesday 14:00 - 16:00\n* Please make reservations in advance online or by phone','','07990  316-8, Mokdongdong-ro, Yangcheon-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 5  Omokgyo Station  Exit 4,  538m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16391&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16392&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16393&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16394&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.529429,'ENP002250'),
(56,'Hwagyesa Temple','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Hwagyesa-Temple/ENP002021','Hwagyesa Temple is located in the Samgaksan Woods, at the foot of Samgaksan Mountain in Seoul. Since the temple is close to center of the city, many people visit to feel the nature. Hwagyesa Temple has established a reputation as a temple that brings Korean Buddhism to an international audience. The temple attracts many Zen masters from all over the world and in addition to Korean and expat Buddhists. Hwagyesa Temple also offers a range of temple stay programs that are open to the general public. Visitors can choose from a one day program, a meditation-focused program, and an activities-focused temple stay program.  { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"Hwagyesa Temple\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5.0\", \"ratingCount\": \"16\" }, \"review\": [{ \"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": { \"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\" }, \"author\": { \"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"idil a\" }, \"reviewBody\": \"It was my first time in temple stay. Amazing experince. Hwagyesa is very close to city centre but also in a very peaceful, silent location. The surrounding is beautiful, the temple family is so kind and nice, they welcomed us so warmly! The food is very delicious as well.This is an unforgettable experience, definitely recommended!\", \"datePublished\": \"2020-11-08\" }] }','-3485','Opening hours vary depending on what Buddhist ceremonies are taking place, and the temple schedule','','01095  117 Hwagyesa-gil, Gangbuk-gu, Seoul','Subway Ui-Sinseol Line  Hwagye Station  Exit 2,  922m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20524&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20525&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20526&fileTy=MED