(113,'Sulla-gil Road','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Sulla-gil-Road/ENP001932','Sulla-gil Road runs through Jongno-gu and is known as Seoul\'s Historical Literary Trail. Sulla-gil is divided into eastern and western sections. Dongsulla-gil is the eastern section and Seoseulla-gil is the street\'s western section.','-40','','','03134  Seosulla-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 1/3/5, Jongno 3(sam)-ga Station  Exit 7,  471m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72657&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72658&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72659&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72660&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72661&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.575002,'ENP001932'),
(114,'Seonjeongneung (Tomb)','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seonjeongneung-Tomb/ENP001414','Seonjeongneung is the name of Seolleung and Jeongneung combined, and it refers to the royal tombs of King Seongjong (the 9th king of the Joseon Dynasty), Queen Jeonghyeon (the second wife of King Seongjong) and King Jungjong (a son of the two). Seonjeongneung was designated as a UNESCO World Heritage site in 2009, enhancing its status as historic remains. It is easily accessible as it is situated close to Seolleung Station, Subway Line 2. It makes an ideal place for the public to enjoy a stroll.    Seolleung, the tomb of King Seongjong (reigned 1469-1494) was built in 1495; subsequently, the tomb of Queen Jeonghyeon (1462-1530) was built on the east side of Seolleung in 1530. Jeongneung, which is the tomb of King Jungjong (the 11th king of the Joseon Dynasty, reigned 1506-1544), was built in 1544, and was moved from its original site in Wondang, Goyang-gun, Gyeonggi-do, to this current location in 1562 by Queen Munjeong (the second wife of King Jungjong, 1501-1565). Seonjeongneung is designated as Historic Site No. 199 as well as being a UNESCO World Heritage site.    Frequently Asked Questions about Seonjeongneung (Tomb)         How much is the Seonjeongneung Royal Tomb entrance fee?         The admission fee for Seonjeongneung Royal Tomb is as follows. (As of 2025)     ??Individual  - Ages 25 to 64 (Koreans), 19 to 64 (Foreigners) : 1,000 KRW    ??Groups (more than ten people)  - Ages 25 to 64 (Koreans), 19 to 64 (Foreigners) : 800 KRW    Please refer to the official website for free admissions and discounts.          I am curious about the Seonjeongneung Royal Tomb\'s parking information.         There are 48 (2 accessible) parking spaces at the Seonjeongneung Royal Tomb. The parking lot operates 365 days a year, even on holidays. Parking rates are as follows. *The parking lot close after 22:00       (As of 2025)         ??2 hours or less : 400 KRW per 5 minut