(115,'Seoul Museum of Craft','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seoul-Museum-of-Craft/ENP038092','Seoul Museum of Craft Art aims to be an open space where traditional crafts and modern crafts can come together to share the value of crafts and to be the key to unlocking the future of crafts. The museum features galleries on the \"beginning of crafts\" from mankind long ago, when clay was molded, engraved, and baked, as well as galleries and exhibitions that focus in on the technical, practical, artistic, and cultural values of crafts throughout time and space.','-13370','10:00 - 18:00 (Last admission at 17:30)\nFri 10:00 - 21:00','Mondays, January 1st, Open on Public Holidays','03061  4, Yulgok-ro 3-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 1,  141m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67121&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67122&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67123&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67124&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73865&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.576858,'ENP038092'),
(116,'Seosomun Shrine History Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seosomun-Shrine-History-Museum/ENP030804','Seosomun Shrine History Museum is a history museum where visitors can go see the history of Catholicism in the late Joseon Dynasty.Passing the inscription of Lee Seung-hoon\'s \"Wolrakjaecheonsusangjijin\" (Moon Falls on the Water) at the entrance, visitors are led to an open plaza. The displays of artworks leads into the library and seminar rooms on the first floor. The special exhibitionhalland small assembly hall is located on the B2 level while the Consolation Hall, permanent exhibition, and Sky Square is located on the third basement floor.The most popular spot inside this attraction is Sky Square. Constructed so that the ceiling connects to the ground level and opens itself up to the sky, this space clearly symbolizes the theme of Seosomun Martyrs\' Shrine and the open pathway betweentheearth and sky.','-5468','Tuesday ~ Sunday 09:30 - 17:30','Closed Mondays','04510  5, Chilpae-ro, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 2/5  Chungjeongno Station  Exit 4,  417m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23421&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23422&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23420&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23423&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73788&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.560418,'ENP030804'),
(117,'Seoul Baekje Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seoul-Baekje-Museum/ENP011610','The Seoul Baekje Museum is a history museum that was established at the prehistoric site of Baekje-era ruins in Songpa-gu, Seoul. The museum preserves and studies the relics of Baekje and prehistoric Korea. Visitors can learn more about Korea\'s history at the museum\'s 4D theater and exhibition halls. The Seoul Baekje Museum has an extensive collection of artifacts and relics, and there are also educational programs to participate in and enjoy. Learn about Korean history and cultures at the museum!','-7872','Weekdays 09:00 - 19:00\n Fri 09:00~21:00\nWeekend (November - February 09:00 - 18:00) (KST)','Closed Mondays & New Year\'s Day\n(Museum opens on holidays that fall on a Monday)','05540  71, Wiryeseong-daero, Songpa-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 9  Hanseong Baekje Station  Exit 2,  363m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=5757&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12174&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74754&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74755&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74756&fileTy=MEDIA',5.000000,37.519009,'ENP011610'),
(118,'Seoul Yangnyeongsi Herb Medicine Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Yangnyeongsi-Herb-Medicine-Museum/ENP004632','The Seoul Yangnyeongsi Herb Medicine Museum was established to preserve and pass on the history and knowledge of traditional Korean medicine. Fittingly, the museum is located across from the Seoul Yangnyeong Market, one of the most famous oriental medicine markets in Korea from which approximately 70% of the nation\'s oriental medicine is distributed. The museum collects, manages, and stores many artifacts and materials to exhibit. Visitors will be able to see everything from the herbs and plants used in traditional medicine, to antique medical records and tools. Admission to the museum is free.','-10130','March - October 10:00 - 18:00\nNovember - February 10:00 - 17:00\n??Last entry is 30 min. before closing','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day & national holidays','02566  26, Yangnyeongjungang-ro, Dongdaemun-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1, Jegi-dong Station  Exit 2,  320m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40031&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40032&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40033&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40034&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40035&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.580655,'ENP004632'),
(119,'Kim Geun-tae Memorial Library-Archives','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Kim-Geun-tae-Memorial-Library-Archives/ENP041903','Kim Geun-tae Memorial Library-Archives which is located at the corner of the way going to Bukhansan National Park, as a Larchiveum, it is a library to read a book but at the same time, it\'s a museum that has a story of democracy and human rights, and also an art gallery to appreciate art works. A courtyard, which was naturally made at the center which was created by connecting the both ends of the two buildings with the bridge, is the most opened space in Kim Geun-tae Memorial Library-Archives and it\'s a space where you can directly feel the sunlight and the wind. As a library and an art gallery, the installation work is located on the courtyard so you can see an art work in the nature. At the rooftop called \'Sanbaramgil\',  various plays and events will be held with the background of the nature.','-3976','Daily 09:00 ~ 20:00\nWeekends 09:00 ~ 17:00','Every Monday, National Holiday','01301  14, Dobongsan-gil, Dobong-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1/7   Dobongsan Station  Exit 1,  300m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=54699&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=54700&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=54701&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=54702&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=54703&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.690505,'ENP041903'),
(120,'SeMA Museum of Photography','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/SeMA-photo-museum/ENPl3j0oy','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}The SeMA Museum of Photography, newly opened in Changdong, Dobong-gu, Seoul, is a branch of the Seoul Museum of Art and the first and only public art museum in Korea specializing in photography, established after more than a decade of preparation. The museum plans to continue diverse activities to become a new center for photographic art in Korea and Asia through creative and experimental exhibitions and programs encompassing the entire photography culture and in-depth research, collection, and preservation activities.Notably, the museum is equipped with facilities where visitors can experience the influence and artistic value of photography, including exhibition halls, education rooms, darkrooms, a photo library, and a photobook café for educational programs covering all age groups.The architecture was designed by Austrian architect Mladen Jadric (representative of Jadric Architektur ZTGmbH) and 1990 Urban Architecture (representative Yoon Geun-ju), who visualized and implemented the pixel of photography, which is a picture drawn with light.','+82 2??124??600','Tuesday-Friday 10:00 AM-8:00 PM\n