(121,'Kukje Gallery','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Kukje-Gallery/ENP003241','The Kukje Gallery is one of Korea\'s major art galleries and visitors can see artworks from new and established artists. Founded in 1982, the Kukje Gallery exhibits works from prominent foreign artists, but the gallery also exhibits and fosters promising Korean artists. Enjoy incredible contemporary art at the Kukje Gallery.','-9104','* Monday - Saturday 10:00 - 18:00 (KST)\n* Sundays & National Holidays 10:00 - 17:00 (KST)','','100-200  54, Samcheong-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 1,  812m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16442&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16443&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16444&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73930&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73931&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.580723,'ENP003241'),
(122,'National Museum of Art at Deoksugung Palace','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/National-Museum-of-Art-Deoksugung-Palace/ENP001707','The National Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art at Deoksugung opened in 1998 as an annex of the National Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art, Korea. The museum building, Seokjojeon Hall, is located at Deoksugung Palace. Seokjojeon Hall is an exquisite example of Western architecture from the early 20th century. It is the only Korean palace to have an outdoor garden and fountain designed in a Western style. The museum??s location inside the palace means that many visitors choose to combine their visit with a tour of Deoksugung. Jeongdong Park, the Seoul Museum of Art, and Namdaemun Market are some of the nearby tourist attractions. Admission fees vary depending on exhibition but visitors will be able to see beautiful works of art from Korean and international artists.','-2542','Tuesdays, Thursdays, Fridays & Sundays 10:00 - 19:00\nWednesdays & Saturdays 10:00 - 21:00\n* Last entry is 1 hour before closing.','Closed Mondays & New Year\'s Day','04519  99, Sejong-daero, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 1/2  City Hall Station  Exit 1,  72m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22661&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22662&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22663&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74752&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74753&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.567402,'ENP001707'),
(123,'Seodaemun Museum of Natural History','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seodaemun-Museum-of-Natural-History/ENP002613','p { text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; }  The four-story building of the Seodaemun Museum of Natural History was the first public museum of natural history in Korea. Opened in 2003, the museum displays the origins of life on earth through a variety of real specimens of minerals, rocks and fossils, and through models, including life size models of dinosaurs, from all over the world. The museum is a fun and family-friendly attraction.','-9149','* March to October \nWeekdays 09:00 ??18:00 & Weekends 09:00 ??19:00\n* November to February\nWeekdays 09:00 ??17:00 & Weekends 09:00 ??18:00\n\n(Last entry 1 hour before closing)','Closed Mondays, January 1st, Lunar New Year & Chuseok','03718  51, Yeonhui-ro 32-gil, Seodaemun-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 2, Sinchon Station Exit 3, take Seodaemun 03 bus from Sinchon Station stop, get off at Seodaemun Natural History Museum Entrance stop, 283m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17244&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17245&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17246&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17247&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72587&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.576673,'ENP002613'),
(124,'Reopening of Dongdaemun History Museum Exhibition Hall','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/exhibitionhallreopening/ENP026206','The Dongdaemun History Museum, operated under the Seoul Museum of History, reopened the doors to its permanent exhibition hall following the two-year renovation project on Tuesday, August 11, 2020. The entire, all-new remodeled interior floor is set with carvings and gobo projectors that capture the blueprint of the excavation site of historical remains by layer to emulate the historical, figurative layers that are stacked upon each other at this very geographical site. The exhibition is characterized into the following four different themes: I. Military Training Administration & Lower Directorate; II. City Wall Floodgates; III. Two Centuries of Change; and IV. Excavated History. There are also various, fun programs for children within the exhibition and hands-on space provided that feature sand-crafting, 3D photo zones, and more.','-2273','Daily 10:00 - 18:00','Closed Mondays & New Year\'s Day','04566  281, Eulji-ro, Jung-gu, Seoul  (Dongdaemun History & Culture Park)','Subway Lines 2/4/5  Dongdaemun History & Culture Park Station  Exits 1/2,  356m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=31627&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=31628&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=31631&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=31632&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.566029,'ENP026206'),
(125,'Amore Pacific Museum of Art (APMA)','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Amore-Pacific-Museum-of-Art-APMA/ENP030803','p{ text-align:justify; word-spacing:2px; }Amore Pacific Museum of Art (APMA) is a newly opened museum inside Amore Pacific\'s Yongsan headquarters. Aiming for \"an open space to find beauty in the ordinary\", this museum was established as a space for fostering open communication. To this end, the museum collects, studies, and exhibits anicent Korean and contemporary arts, also supporting researchers, academic societies, and young writers in the process. The basement floor features an exhibition showcasing ancient Korean art and contemporary art. Connecting the first three floors, the \"Atrium\" features the museum lobby, museum shop, another exhibition space called \"APMA Cabinet,\" and a library for museums around the world (apLAP).','-8305','Daily 10:00 - 18:00','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year & Chuseok','04386  100, Hangang-daero, Yongsan-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Sinyongsan Station  Exit 1,  84m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23416&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23418&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73974&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23417&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23419&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.528973,'ENP030803'),
(126,'Horim Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Horim-Museum-Sinsa/ENP005546','The Horim Museum is a privately-run art museum in Korea. The museum is comprised of three buildings, and the museum\'s five-story building hosts much of the art collection. The second, third, and fourth floors display antique and modern art as well as special exhibitions. On the last Thursday of each month, admission to the Horim Museum is free.','-3986','10:30 - 18:00 (Last entry 17:00)\n\n- Temporarily closed from 7/27 to 9/1 due to exhibition change at the Shinsa branch','Closed Mondays,Sundays, January 1st, Lunar New Year & Chuseok','06021  317, Dosan-daero, Gangnam-gu, Seoul','Subway Suin-Bundang Line  Apgujeong Rodeo Station  Exit 5,  635m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3124&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3125&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3126&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72589&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72590&fileTy=MEDIA&f',5.000000,37.522970,'ENP005546'),
