(129,'Heo Jun Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Heo-Jun-Museum/ENP001403','The Heo Jun Museum commemorates the life and works of the renowned Joseon-era doctor and scholar, Heo Jun. The museum is located in Gayang-dong near Guam Park and the neighborhood is known as the birthplace of Heo Jun. Visitors can see a range of items relating to Oriental medicine, items once owned by Heo Jun, and medical books. Some of the books on display were written out by Heo Jun\'s hand. A writing model of his most famous work, \"Dongui Bogam,\" is on display and it is still an influential medical tome in Oriental medicine today.','-12267','* March - October Weekdays 10:00 - 18:00 & Weekends/Holidays 10:00 - 17:00\n* November - February Weekdays 10:00 - 17:00 & Weekends/Holidays 10:00 - 17:00 (KST)\n??Ticketing stops 1 hour prior to closing.','Closed Mondays, Jan. 1st, Lunar New Year\'s Day & Chuseok','07525  87, Heojun-ro, Gangseo-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 9  Gayang Station  Exit 1,  736m\nSubway Line 5  Balsan Station Exit 3, take bus 6657, 6630, 1002 and get off at Hanbogu Ammaeul Apartment, 243m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16357&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16358&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16359&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16360&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75425&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.566869,'ENP001403'),
(130,'National Hangeul Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/NationalHangeulMuseum/ENP035405','The National Hangeul Museum was opened on October 9, 2014, to create and promote the literary and cultural value of Hangeul, the nation\'s most significant cultural heritage. The National Hangeul Museum investigates, collects, and researches materials scattered around the country and abroad and shows the cultural diversity and future value of Hangeul through exhibitions. It is a place where Hangeul culture blossoms through education that aims for communication and empathy across generations and nationalities.','-8244','10:00 - 18:00\n- Closed for construction from October 2024 to October 8, 2025','January 1, Lunar New Year\'s Day, Chuseok\n* Closed days of the Hangeul Library: Saturdays, Sundays, and public holidays (except Hangeul Day)','04383  139, Seobinggo-ro, Yongsan-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4 / Gyeongui Central Line  Ichon Station  Exit 2,  500m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=52753&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=52755&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=52757&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=52759&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=52761&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.526861,'ENP035405'),
(131,'Gallery Mosoon','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/2024-mosoon/ENPxua216','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}Located on Jeongdong-gil, within the 100-year-old modern cultural heritage site ??Shina Memorial Hall,??this gallery showcases Korean crafts and art. It was established with the hope that visitors traveling from afar will feel that their journey to and from the gallery is part of the exhibition experience itself. Unlike other spaces in Shina Memorial Hall, the gallery has been remodeled with white cube walls and ceilings to give it a more contemporary feel. With each changing exhibition, the gallery introduces new playlists, scents, and furniture, creating a fresh experience every time. Come and appreciate Korean crafts in this cozy and serene space.','-2294','12:00~18:00','Sun-Mon','04518  Shina Memorial Hall, Room 203, 33 Jeongdong-gil, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1/2  City Hall Station  Exit 12,  507m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=66550&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=66551&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=66552&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&th