(132,'PKM Gallery','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/PKM-Gallery/ENP002885','p { text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; }  The PKM Gallery was established in 2001 and a range of art from diverse mediums can be found on display. Exhibitions include paintings, sculptures, and videos, while the gallery\'s goal is to be known for its quality of art. Prominent Korean and foreign artists fill the gallery\'s rosters and some of the more prominent names are Lee Bul, Jorge Pardo, Michael Joo, and Stephen Prina.','-10121','Tuesday - Sunday 10:00 - 18:00 (KST)','Closed Mondays','03049  40, Samcheong-ro 7-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 1,  1.2km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=1823&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=1824&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=1825&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75563&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75564&fileTy=MEDIA&f',5.000000,37.584067,'ENP002885'),
(133,'ChoiManLin Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/ChoiManLin-Museum/ENP042352','Theelegant two-story, Western-style building was built in the 1970s. Here,sculptor Choi Man Lin created his world of art for about 30 years from 1988. Evenwith all its traces of artistry intact, it eventually grew to become the ChoiMan Lin Museum with the help of the Seongbuk-gu District and EMA Architects. Reborn as an art museum in2019, this building contains the traces of sculptor Choi Man Lin, which werepreserved through a remodeling method that protects the appearance of theexisting building as much as possible. Thisbuilding, which shows off its architectural beauty while maximizing itsfunction as an art museum, won the Excellence Award at the 2020 Public BuildingAwards of Korea.','-11888','Daily 10:00 ~ 18:00\nClosed for exhibition preparation (July 1 - September 3)','Closed Sundays & Mondays','02708  23, Solsaem-ro 7-gil, Seongbuk-gu, Seoul','Subway Uisinseol   Bukhansanbogukmun Station Exit 2,  438m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56158&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56159&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56160&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56161&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56162&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.610674,'ENP042352'),
(134,'Ilmin Museum of Art','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Ilmin-Museum-of-Art/ENP002251','Ilmin Museum of Art is a private art museum that mainly exhibits Korean contemporary art. It was originally established to commemorate Kim Sangman, former president of the Donga Ilbo, one of Korea\'s leading media outlets. The museum\'s name was taken from Kim\'s pen name, Ilmin (meaning ??one people??or ??a nation united??in Korean). The museum is run by the Ilmin Cultural Foundation and a variety of special exhibitions and art classes are held throughout the year. The museum has a cafe and restaurant on the first floor.','-3990','Daily 11:00 - 19:00 KST','Closed on Mondays','03187  152, Sejong-daero, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 5  Gwanghwamun Station  Exit 5,  16m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12728&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12729&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12730&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12731&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.569633,'ENP002251'),
(135,'Kim Chong Yung Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Kim-Chong-Yung-Museum/ENP002066','The Kim Chong Yung Museum was established to honor the legacy and art of the modern artist Kim Chong Yung and to provide support to young artists. Kim was a pioneer of modern scultpure and the museum\'s main hall has a permanent exhibition with Kim\'s works and the new hall showcases artwork from new artists. Art and cultural classes are offered at the museum in two semesters during the calendar year. Admission to the Kim Chong Yung Museum is free.','-9621','March - October 10:00 - 18:00\nDecember - February 10:00 - 17:00 (KST)\n*Café Samiru Operating Hours: 11:00 - 21:00','Closed Mondays','110-848  30, Pyeongchang 32-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3 Gyeongbokgung Station Exit 3,  take Bus 1711 and get off at Lotte Apartment, 365m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72868&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72869&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72870&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72871&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72872&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.613028,'ENP002066'),
(136,'Arario Gallery Seoul','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/ArarioGallery/ENP002388','p { text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; }  Over the years, Arario Gallery Seoul has led the way in curating a harmonic fusion and variety of different art forms in Korea\'s art community through bold collaborations with international artistry that have never been attempted before. Also, the gallery takes the forefront in introducing artwork from today\'s more modern Korean artists having implemented an ongoing and structured system of exclusively-contracted artists. Currently, a wide range of artworks from artists native to India and Southeast Asia, who have yet to come to Korea despite having already experienced China\'s art community, are finally getting some spotlight in Korea. What\'s better is that with the help of continued promotional activity, the search and funding for up-and-coming talent in the respective regions is ongoing as well. Thanks to the gallery\'s efforts grounded in a system of exclusive artists displaying excellence; various collaborations with other galleries, both at home and abroad; introductions of varied artworks from numerous places around the world; and more, the Arario Gallery is set to play out its role as Asia\'s signature gallery that expands upon the possibilities for the future of Korea\'s art community while leading the market as well.      Since its first opening in Sogyeok-dong, Jongno-gu, in 2006, Arario Gallery Seoul has been leading the contemporary art scene based on its solid artist system and bold exhibition planning capabilities. In March 2014, it relocated near the National Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art, and from April 2018 to November 2019, Arario Gallery Seoul Ryse Hotel, its second exhibition space in Seoul, opened near Hongik University. This effort aimed to inherit and develop the youthful and innovative spirit symbolized by the area. In 2022, Arario Gallery Seoul ended its Sogyeok-dong era and reopened with a new look in Wonseo-dong, Jongno-gu, in February 2023. The gallery aims to collaborate and support artists, striving for mutual growth through proactive exploration and consistent support. At the same time, it seeks to realize experimental and serious exhibition planning to continuously contribute to the advancement of the Korean art scene.','-6162','Daily 11:00 - 18:00 (KST)','Closed Sundays & Mondays','03058  85 Yulgok-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul Arario Gallery','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 3,  180m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17269&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17270&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17271&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.577831,'ENP002388'),
(137,'Artside Gallery','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/2024-artside/ENP72zzo1','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}Opened in Insadong in 1999, Artside Gallery operates under the motto ??art is the constant centralization of the surroundings.??It aims to bridge artists and the art market by providing various creative directions to domestic and international artists. Based on its beliefs and perspectives, Artside Gallery has been at the forefront of introducing the diverse works and artistic worlds of talented artists from Korea, China, Asia, Europe, and beyond to the domestic and international art scene. Since relocating to Tongui-dong in 2010, the gallery has continued to curate exhibitions that reflect its distinct identity. Through its participation in various domestic and international art fairs, Artside Gallery has opened the door to the global art market and solidified its position as an internationally recognized gallery.','-1665','Tues-Sat 10:00-18:00','Closed Sundays and Mondays  \nClosed for Chuseok holidays from September 16 to 18','03044  15 Jahamun-ro 6-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Gyeongbokgung Station  Exit 3,  282m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67527&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67528&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67529&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67530&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74121&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.578084,'ENP72zzo1'),
(138,'Seoul Children\'s Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seoul-Childrens-Museum/ENP011669','The Seoul Children??s Museum is a multipurpose learning space filled with activities and experiences for children to enjoy. The museum\'s overall theme is \"children designing happiness,\" and there are educational programs available for children according to both age and theme. The building spans three stories above-ground and an additional 3 stories underground. There is a performance hall, an experience hall, and educational facilities. Additional facilities include a cafe and a nursing room.   { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"Seoul Children\'s Museum\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.5\", \"ratingCount\": \"14\" }, \"review\": [{ \"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": { \"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\" }, \"author\": { \"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Strawberry L\" }, \"reviewBody\": \"We had a GREAT time here. Our child with ASD had a grand time and played well with kids from other countries. Incredibly welcoming and lots of useful things for mamas - nice changing rooms, water fountains, cafe with toddler friendly options. Definitely recommend when traveling with toddler/little kid in Seoul.\", \"datePublished\": \"2024-08-03\" }] }','-15870','Tuesday to Sunday: 10:00 - 18:00 (Last entry at 17:00)','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day & holidays','04991,  216, Neungdong-ro, Gwangjin-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 7  Children\'s Grand Park Station  Exit 1,  326m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67002&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67003&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67004&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67005&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67006&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.548850,'ENP011669'),
(139,'Museum of Korea Straw and Plants Handicraft','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Museum-of-Korea-Straw-and-Plants-Handicraft/ENP003332','The Museum of Korea Straw and Plants Handicraft is a private museum that was founded in 1992. The museum promotes cultural awareness of straw and its importance as a raw material in Korea. Straw was used in many different ways and is still used today in folk art. The museum\'s exhibitions display thousands of items made from straw including arts and crafts, tools, relics, and toys. The museum operates various educational programs for laypeople and professionals as well as workshops and crafting classes.','-9450','10:00 ??17:00 KST','Closed Sundays, Mondays, New Year\'s, Lunar New Year & Chuseok','03075  45, Sungkyunkwan-ro 4-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Hyehwa Station  Exit 4,  315m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16315&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16316&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16317&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16318&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75407&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.584919,'ENP003332'),
(140,'Chojun Textile & Quilt Art Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Chojun-Textile-Art-Museum/ENP006463','The Chojun Textile & Quilt Art Museum was established in 1998 and specializes in textile and quiltworks. It is the only museum in Korea which is devoted entirely to textiles. Examples of traditional Korean embroidery are on display and museum-goers can also enjoy seeing royal clothing from the Joseon Dynasty. Learn about Eastern and Western textile history and methods at the Chojun Textile & Quilt Art Museum.','-4747','Mon-Fri 10:00-17:00 (Last entry is 30 mins prior to closing)','Closed  Saturdays ~ Sundays & national holidays','04630  66, Toegye-ro 18-gil, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Myeongdong Station  Exit 3,  324m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3588&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3589&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3590&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75487&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75488&fileTy=MEDIA&f',5.000000,37.558144,'ENP006463'),
(141,'Seoul Arts Center - Seoul Calligraphy Art Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/SeoulCalligraphyMuseum/ENPx6grff','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}Located within the Seoul Arts Center, the Seoul Calligraphy Art Museum opened in 1988 alongside the Music Hall as the first museum in Korea dedicated to calligraphy. The four-story building houses three exhibition halls across two floors and two storage rooms. Its collection includes historical Korean calligraphy literature such as Geun-yeok Seohwa-sa and more than 1,300 modern calligraphy works from Korea and East Asia. Through continuous exhibitions, the museum conveys the heritage and culture of South Korean calligraphy and painting to visitors.','1688-1352','Tues-Sun 10:00-19:00','Monday','06757  2406 Nambusunhwan-ro, Seocho-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3, Nambu Bus Terminal Station (Seoul Arts Center) Exi 5, 1.4km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74797&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74798&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74799&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74800&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74801&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.478482,'ENPx6grff'),
(142,'Bank of Korea Money Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Bank-of-Korea-Money-Museum/ENP002730','The main building of the Bank of Korea provides extensive information on the manufacturing process of money and the development of the Korean economy. The collections is vast and there are over 20,000 pieces of Korean and foreign banknotes, coins and tokens on display. The museum consists of four exhibition halls and an information reference library. Admission to the Bank of Korea Money Museum is free.','-5560','10:00 - 17:00 (KST)','Mondays, Lunar New Year, Chuseok','100-794  39 Namdaemun-ro, Jung-gu, Seoul  (Bank of Korea Building)','Subway Line 4  Hoehyeon Station  Exit 7,  310m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42359&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72850&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72851&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72852&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72853&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.562150,'ENP002730'),
(143,'Gallery Hyundai','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Gallery-Hyundai-EN/ENP001694','Gallery Hyundai is a famous gallery located on Sagandong Gallery Street. The street is known for its many galleries, hence the name, yet Gallery Hyundai stands out from the crowd. The gallery exhibits major contemporary Korean artists, such as Park Su-Geun and Lee Jung-Seob, as well as many major foreign artists. The gallery also has a superb restaurant with a great wine selection.','-5707','Daily 10:00 - 18:00','Closed Mondays','03062  14, Samcheong-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 1,  595m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72841&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72842&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72843&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.577676,'ENP001694'),
(144,'National Museum Of Modern And Contemporary Art: Changdong Residency','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/National-Museum-Changdong-Residency/ENP002285','The Changdong Residency of the National Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art (MMCA) is an arts and cultural space that is designed to allow visitors to get more familiar with modern art. The museum offers various exhibitions, region-linked programs and educational programs. The residency space also provides art studios for Korean and international artists.','-1910','Weekdays 09:00 - 18:00\n* Please refer to the website as hours may be subject to change.','','01469  257, Deongneung-ro, Dobong-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Suyu Station  Exit 1,  Bus 1127 or 1138, get off at the Foreign Exchange Bank stop, 120 m\nSubway Lines 1/4  Changdong Station  Exit 2,   Bus 1157, get off at the Foreign Exchange Bank stop, 120 m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12488&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12489&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12490&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12491&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.641341,'ENP002285'),
(145,'Seoul Museum of Art (Seosomun Main Building)','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Museum-of-Art-Seosomun/ENP001525','The Seoul Museum of Art (SeMA) opened in 1988 and has earned a reputation as one of Korea??s leading art venues with a series of world-famous exhibitions. Situated in the center of Seoul, its convenient location and outstanding collections attract large numbers of locals and tourists. The specially-designed building features large windows that fill the interior with natural light. This attracts not only tourists but also artists and even movie directors, some of whom have used the location for filming.      Since it was established in 1988, the main museum building has been relocated to Seosomun-dong in Seoul. The museum has a variety of annexes such as SeMA Gyeonghuigung, located on the historic site of Gyeonghuigung Palace, and the Nam Seoul Annex Building, which is situated in a building that was once the Belgian Embassy. The museum also runs the Naji Art Studio which offers workshops and financial support to new generations of Korean artists to nurture their creativity.      The beautiful Renaissance façade which forms the entrance to the museum was originally part of the Supreme Court, built in 1928. Today it is better known as the iconic image of the Seoul Museum of Art. In March 2006, the arch and the beautifully constructed museum building were designated as Cultural Property No. 237 in recognition of their great historical and architectural value.','-10844','(March - October) Tuesdays - Thursdays 10:00 - 20:00  / Friday 10:00-21:00 / Weekends 10:00 - 19:00\n(November - February) Tuesdays - Fridays 10:00 - 20:00 / Friday 10:00-21:00 / Weekends 10:00 - 18:00\n??Culture Day\n- Museum main building, Buk Seoul Museum','New Years Day\nClosed on Mondays','04515  61, Deoksugung-gil, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 1/2  City Hall Station  Exit 10,  264m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=31415&fileTy=MEDIA