(146,'Hakgojae Gallery','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Hakgojae-Gallery/ENP001871','Hakgojae Gallery is a modern art gallery and its motto is ??creation of the new by understanding the old.??The architecture of the gallery reflects this motto. The main building of Gallery Hakgojae was designed to look like a hanok, (a traditional Korean house), while the new hall was designed in a modern, 21st-century style of architecture. Though the two architectural styles are different, they harmonize beautifully. Hakgojae Gallery also has a branch in the Shanghai art district of Moganshan Road. Admission to the gallery is free.','-2164','Daily 10:00 ??18:00','Closed Mondays','110-200  50, Samcheong-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3, Anguk Station, Exit 1, 751m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16657&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16658&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16659&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16660&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.580328,'ENP001871'),
(147,'Pace Gallery Seoul','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/pacegallery/ENPet80lf','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}Pace Gallery is one of the world??s foremost contemporary art galleries, representing some of the most influential artists of our time. It has also maintained decades-long relationships with the estates of artists such as Alexander Calder, Jean Dubuffet, Agnes Martin, Louise Nevelson, and Mark Rothko. Since its early years, Pace has supported artists associated with Abstract Expressionism and those working with light and space, establishing itself as a uniquely distinguished gallery across the United States. Today, Pace operates exhibition spaces worldwide, including two galleries in Chelsea, New York, as well as in London, Geneva, Berlin, Hong Kong, Seoul, Los Angeles, and Tokyo.','-10098','10:00-18:00','Closed every Sunday and Monday','04348  Pace Gallery, 267 Itaewon-ro, Yongsan-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 6, Hangangjin Station, Exit 1, 185m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75512&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75513&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA