(148,'Cheonggyecheon Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Cheonggyecheon-Museum/ENP004693','The Cheonggyecheon Museum documents the history of the Cheonggyecheon Stream area. The museum spans 6 floors, with several exhibition halls, education facilities, and an auditorium. The museum also offers educational classes for children on the history and ecology of the stream. The building itself is characterized by its long glass exterior, designed to symbolize the flowing waters of the Cheonggyecheon Stream. Admission to the Cheonggyecheon Museum is free.','-5616','Daily 09:00 - 18:00 (KST)','Closed Mondays & January 1st\n??November - February: Closed Weekends & Holidays','04704  530, Cheonggyecheon-ro, Seongdong-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 2  Yongdu Station  Exit 5,  497m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=69808&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=69809&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=69810&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75409&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75410&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.570148,'ENP004693'),
(149,'Arario Museum in Space','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Arario-Museum-in-Space/ENP020731','The Arario Museum in Space is a modern art museum that was established by the chairman of the Arario Corporation, Chang-il Kim. The building that houses the museum was designed by the famed Korean architect Kim Swoo-geun. Until he passed away in 1986, the building served as Kim\'s office and home. Today, the Arario Museum in Space calls the building home and the spaces are full of incredible modern art. This historic building is one of the most unique cultural spaces in Seoul.','-6356','10:00 - 19:00 \n(Last entry at 18:00)','Closed Mondays','03058  83, Yulgok-ro (Wonseo-dong), Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 3,  181m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14446&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14447&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14448&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73969&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73970&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.577738,'ENP020731'),
(150,'Kyung Hee University Natural History Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/KyungheeUniversityHistoryMuseum/ENP006957','Upon opening its doors in 1978, the Kyunghee University Natural History Museum served as a little respite of nature in the city that boasted of a collection of nearly 90,000 specimen on display. The museum was initially founded upon the purpose of realizing the Kyungee University founding ideology of \"Creating a world of culture\" grounded in the results that had been obtained through several years of studying nature. The effort continues to approach the distancing relationship between nature and humankind amid rapid societal changes and urbanization with a \"respite of nature in the city\" that provides a sense of living in harmony with nature. All six floors of the museum display easy-to-understand exhibits capturing a comparison between the current state of evolution and the process of transformation up to the present-day with specimen of different plants and animals, as well as various rocks from sedimentary to igneous and metamorphic rocks that were used for research purposes by specialized teams of professors in various fields. There are courses and tour programs offered to help understand and practice nature preservation and the importance of life within the framework of these exhibited specimen. The Kyunghee University Natural History Museum has collected numerous specimen since the 1940s, while possessing a collection of more recent domestic specimen that have already become extinct or show signs of endangerment. The museum offers the opportunity for children and adults alike to more systematically learn about the classification and ecosystems of animals and plants and prioritizes itself with the fervor of exploring nature, as well as the awareness of nature protection.','+82-2-961-0142~3','Daily 10:00 - 17:00','Closed weekends & holidays','02447  26, Kyungheedae-ro, Dongdaemun-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1, Foreign Language University Station Exit 1,  1.1km\nSubway Line 1, Hoegi Station Exit 1,  1.2km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=37540&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=37541&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=37542&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=37543&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=37544&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.596712,'ENP006957'),
(151,'Total Museum of Contemporary Art','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Total-Museum-of-Contemporary-Art/ENP003085','Located in a secluded residential area of Pyeongchang-dong overlooking Bukhansan Mountain, the Total Museum exhibits the best of contemporary Korean art. An outdoor performance stage and outdoor exhibition spaces at the museum offers scenic views as well as a wide variety of cultural events such as lectures and performances. The permanent collection includes sculptures, prints, paintings, videos, and illustrated books ranging from modern art to old masterpieces. The museum also holds special events, such as seminars, concerts and educational programs. Admission fees vary by event.','-7336','Tue - Sun, 13:00 - 18:00 (last entry at 17:30)','Closed Mondays, holidays & days of exhibition installation','03004  8, Pyeongchang 32-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Gyeongbokgung Station  Exit 3,  (Take bus nos. 1020 or 1711 ??Get off at Lotte-Samsung Apartments stop)\nSubway Line 4  Gireum Station  Exit 3,  (Take bus nos. 7211 or 110 ??Get off at Lotte-Samsung Apartments stop)','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=13435&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=13436&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=13437&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=13438&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75489&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.612099,'ENP003085'),
(152,'Gahoe Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Gahoe-Museum-EN/ENP018912','??성??식 최신??코드  The Gahoe Museum is Korean folk art museum established by Yoon Yeolsu. The museum\'s exhibits Director Yoon\'s private collection of folk paintings and folk religious amulets. There are more than 2,000 folk paintings and craftworks on display and the museum aims to showcase and preserve Korean folk art. Visitors can also take folk painting lessons at the museum.','-1127','10:00 - 18:00 KST\n\n* Last entry is 40 min. before closing\n* For activities, last entry is 1 hr. before closing','Closed Mondays','03056  52, Bukchon-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul, Korea','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 2,  496m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20453&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20454&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20455&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20456&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.581409,'ENP018912'),
(153,'An Jung-geun Memorial Hall','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/An-Jung-geun-Memorial-Hall/ENP004281','The An Jung-geun Memorial Hall was established to memorialize the Korean patriot An Jung-geun. An fought for Korean independence from Japan and was ultimately executed by Japanese authorities for assassinating Ito Hirobumi in 1909. Ito was a major force behind the Japanese annexation of Korea. The memorial hall is composed of 12 exhibition halls and galleries, an auditorium, a reference library, and a rest area. In addition to exhibition information about An\'s life and some of his calligraphy, the memorial hall also hosts the An Jung-guen Academny and other events each year. Events include visits to historic sites abroad that were important to independence movements and calligraphy contests. Admission to the An Jung-geun Memorial Hall is free.       { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"An Jung-geun Memorial Hall\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.0\", \"ratingCount\": \"26\" }, \"review\": { \"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": { \"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\" }, \"author\": { \"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"travelsafer\" }, \"reviewBody\": \"This is a very touching museum dedicated to the life of an important Korean martyr who opposed the Japanese rule on the peninsula and ended up killing the Japanese price ruling over Korea. It is a testimony of the struggle of the oppressed people and symbolizes the will of Korea to be free and be ready for anything to reach its independence. I confess that, before visiting this place, I did not know anything about Ahn Jung Geun, but when I got out of the museum I felt quite emotional. His life is narrated as a story of strong belief and resistance until martyrdom. Many parts and panels are in Korean only, but the friendly lady at the entrance and a man who we met on the second floor were very helpful. In particular he gave us a small book in English about his life and pictures. If you can, add this museum to your list of place to visit in Seoul.\", \"datePublished\": \"2016-11-18\" } }] }','-4725','March to October: 10:00 - 18:00\nNovember to February: 10:00 - 17:00 (KST)','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year\'s Day & Chuseok','04636  91, Sowol-ro, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Hoehyeon Station  Exit 3,  689m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17277&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17278&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17279&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17280&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74159&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.554261,'ENP004281'),
(154,'Korean National Police Heritage Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Korean-National-Police-Heritage-Museum/ENP020549','Established Oct. 14, 2005, the Korean National Police Heritage Museum is the best place in Seoul to go to learn about the history of the police force in Korea. Museum-goers can try hands-on experiences of what the police do and aims to expand citizens understanding of and encourage children\'s dreams of becoming police officers. The Police Museum, which moved to it\'s new location in 2021, aims to become a window of communication between the police and the public with trendy exhibitions and hands-on experience facilities.','-6751','KST 09:30-17:30','Closed Mondays, New Year, Lunar New Year, and Chuseok holidays','03166  162 Songwol-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3, Dongnipmun Station, Exit 3,  363m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14412&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14413&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14414&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14415&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.572285,'ENP020549'),
(155,'Museum of Medicine','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Museum-of-Medicine/ENP000846','The Museum of Medicine is a medical museum located at Seoul National University\'s medical school. The museum building was once a hospital (Daehanuiwon Hospital) and it dates back to the early 20th century. The building features a neo-baroque clock tower. The museum also houses research facilities that are used by the Seoul National University Hospital.','-4628','* Weekdays 09:00 - 18:00 KST\n* Saturdays 10:00 - 15:00 KST\n* Group visits require advanced reservations via phone','Closed Sundays, national holidays, May 1 & October 15','03080  101, Daehak-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Hyehwa Station  Exit 3,  452m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17287&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17288&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17289&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75390&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.580385,'ENP000846'),
(156,'Seoul Metropolitan Archives','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seoul-Metropolitan-Archives/ENP034857','As an public archive providing records services for the public, the Seoul Metropolitan Archives collects a number of records and memoirs tracing the history of the city government, as well as the residents of Seoul, and specializes in the preservation and management of such records. The SMA also plans and operates several public programs, including exhibitions, openings, and more.','-5870','Daily 10:00 - 17:00 (KST)','Closed Mondays','03371  7, Tongil-ro 62-gil, Eunpyeong-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 3 / 6  Bulgwang Station  Exit 2,  370m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73871&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73872&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73873&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73874&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.607383,'ENP034857'),
(157,'National Gugak Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/National-Gugak-Museum/ENP011893','The National Gugak Museum is Korea\'s first dedicated gugak (traditional Korean music) museum. The museum collection has approximately 6,000 items that relate to gugak. Visitors can see musical instruments, photos, documents, and much more at the museum. There are six exhibition halls that are organized by theme and the displays showcase everything from videos to instruments.','-3630','Daily 10:00 - 18:00 (Last Entry at 17:30)','Closed Mondays & New Year\'s Day','06757  2364, Nambusunhwan-ro, Seocho-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Nambu Bus Terminal Station  Exit 5,  1.2km\nSubway Line 2  Bangbae Station, Exit 1,  1.5km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17039&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17040&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17041&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17042&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73572&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.478482,'ENP011893'),
(158,'National Folk Museum of Korea','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/National-Folk-Museum-of-Korea/ENP001644','The National Folk Museum of Korea displays the culture and folk history of the Korean people from prehistoric times to the end of the Joseon Dynasty. Since its establishment, the museum has dedicated itself to studying and researching the folk history of Korea, and collecting artifacts from different Korean regions in order to pass on an insight into the lifestyle and culture of Koreans. The museum achieves this by offering visitors various seminars, exhibitions, performance art, concerts and hands-on activities.      Located on the grounds of Gyeongbokgung Palace, the National Folk Museum of Korea is well known for its beautiful architecture. The building was constructed in the traditional Korean style comprising several stories with a pagoda on top. The three main exhibition halls at the museum cover different aspects of Korean life, as well as displaying various local costumes, musical instruments and festivals.    { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"National Folk Museum of Korea\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.5\", \"ratingCount\": \"996\" }, \"review\": [{ \"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": { \"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\" }, \"author\": { \"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Kimberry\" }, \"reviewBody\": \"The National Folk Museum of Korea vividly depicts traditional Korean life through detailed exhibits and interactive displays. A great place to understand Korea??s roots.\", \"datePublished\": \"2024-08-21\" }] }','-6738','09:00 - 18:00 from March to October \n09:00 - 17:00 from November to February \nExtended evening hours: 09:00 to 20:00 on Saturdays between March and October. \n(No extended evening hours from November to February)','','03045  37, Samcheong-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3 Anguk Station Exit 2, 780m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68376&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68377&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68378&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68379&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.578051,'ENP001644'),
(159,'Gallery Art Zone at the National Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Gallery-Art-Zone/ENP016792','The Gallery Art Zone is located on the 1st floor of MMCA and is about 570??in size There are three zones and five gallery spaces. The Gallery Art Zone was borne out of a collaboration with the National Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art (MMCA) and Hyundai Motor Company. The Gallery Art Zone??s aim is to expand the breadth of audiences when it comes to art. Art shouldn??t just be for walls and showcases. The works on display in the Gallery Art Zone can be bought, and regular visitors can bring a piece of art or design home. The Gallery Art Zone shows different aspects of Korean contemporary art and design in each zone. The first zone (Gallery 1) exhibits Korean design and sells works by promising artists, particularly those from the craft sector. The second zone (Galleries 2 and 3) exhibits and sells cultural products that were developed for MMCA, or on display at MMCA. The third zone (Galleries 4 and 5) displays and sells textiles, fashion products, and art books. Additionally, in part as a result of Hyundai Motor Company??s sponsorship, many art related events and special events will be held at the Gallery Art Zone.','-13491','* Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays, Fridays & Sundays 10:00 - 18:00 \n* Wednesdays & Saturdays 10:00 - 21:00 (KST)','','03062  30, Samcheong-ro, (Sogyeok-dong) Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3, Anguk Station, Exit 1,  764m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=9322&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=9323&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=9324&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.579623,'ENP016792'),
(160,'Modern History Memorial Hall','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Modern-History-Memorial-Hall/ENP027105','Modern History Memorial Hall was built for the purpose of remembering and spreading awareness of Korean democracy and past independence movements. Spreading awareness of Korean forefathers who??ve valued and fought for ideals of freedom, equality, and democracy, the institution hopes to deliver a message that Korea is the land where forefathers dreamt of independence and achieved it.','-8403','09:00~18:00(Last entry at 16:30)','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year & Chuseok\n(* If Monday falls on a public holiday, Tuesday is closed as well.)','01013  114, 4.19-ro, Gangbuk-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4, Suyu Station Exit 4,  take (village) Gangbuk 01 ??Get off at Shinsung Villa stop','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20498&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20499&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20500&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20501&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.641067,'ENP027105'),
(161,'National Library of Korea','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/National-Library-of-Korea-EN/ENP011010','The National Library of Korea collects and stores Korea\'s literary and intellectual heritage. Located by Seocho Park, the library has a main building and an annex. The library houses millions of volumes and visitors can learn more about the library through the visitor tour program.','-1010','Daily 09:00 - 18:00 (KST)\n* Night Hours 18:00 - 22:00 (KST)\n(Note: Hours may vary for different resource rooms)','Closed every 2nd/4th Monday & public holidays\n* Please refer to the website for more details.','06579  201, Banpo-daero, Seocho-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3/7/9 Express Bus Terminal Station Exit 5, 812m\nSubway Line 2 Seocho Station Exit 6, 771m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16498&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16499&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16500&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73567&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73568&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.497040,'ENP011010'),
(162,'Ground Seoul','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/2024-groundseoul1/ENP024613','Ground Seoul is a versatile cultural space spanning 4958 square meters. It features a distinctive underground layout that allows for beautiful natural lighting within the exhibition areas. This space is designed to seamlessly blend exhibitions, performances, events, and parties, making it a hub for artistic expression. Ground Seoul aims to establish itself as a landmark cultural venue in Insadong, where anyone can easily engage with and appreciate the arts.','-7488','11:00~18:00 (Vary per exhibition)','Vary per exhibition','03145  26, Insadong 9-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1, Jonggak Station, Exit 3-1, 301m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67376&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67377&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67378&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=67379&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73573&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.573467,'ENP024613'),
(163,'Kyung Hee University Central Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Central-Museum-of-Kyunghee-University/ENP006924','Opened in 1955, the Kyunghee University Central Museum is the first archaeology and history museum of Korea. The museum emphasizes the importance of teaching, preserving, and recording historical artifacts. The museum is home to the country\'s finest Siberian artifacts collection. Admission to the museum is free and there are also regular cultural programs throughout the year.','-1022','Weekdays 10:00 - 17:00','Closed weekends, national holidays & May 18th (University founding day)','02447  56-3 Kyungheedae-ro 1na-gil, Dongdaemun-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1 Hoegi Station Exit 1,  1.1km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3787&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3788&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3789&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.593603,'ENP006924'),
(164,'Kyungin Museum of Fine Art','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Kyung-In-Museum-of-Fine-Art/ENP002011','Founded in 1983 by Gyeongin Lee Geum-hong, Gyeongin Museum of Art is not only a cultural space for artists but also a widely known tourist attraction. The Gyeongin Museum of Art reflects the founder\'s desire to show that the museum is not the exclusive property of a particular group, but a place where people of all ages and backgrounds can feel at home. The interior consists of six exhibition halls, including an atelier, an outdoor garden, and a traditional tea garden, and concerts are held in the outdoor garden in spring and autumn.','-5101','10:00~18:00','Closed on New Year??s Day, Lunar New Year??s Day, and Chuseok','03146  11-4 Insa-dong 10-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway  Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 5,  354m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60440&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60441&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60442&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60443&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60445&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.573207,'ENP002011'),
(165,'Korean Catholic Martyrs??Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Korean-Catholic-Martyrs%E2%80%99-Museum/ENP029394','To publicize the persecution of Catholic martyrs who lost their lives during the Byeongin Persecution back in 1866, Jeoldusan Matyrs\' Memorial Hall changed its name into Korean Catholic Martyrs??Museum. Its facilities include a pilgrimage church, a sacred r ??oom containing the remains of a martyr, a museum showcasing Catholic records, documents, and relics, and an outdoor exhibition.','-7496','Daily 09:30 - 17:00','Closed Mondays','04085  6, Tojeong-ro, Mapo-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 2/6  Hapjeong Station  Exit 7,  500m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22247&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22248&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22249&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75403&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75404&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.544623,'ENP029394'),
(166,'Children\'s Museum of the National Museum of Korea','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/ChildrensMuseum/ENP020547','The Children\'s Museum of the National Museum of Korea showcases the cultural heritage of Korea. The Children\'s Museum is located within the National Museum of Korea.    Children can learn about the way of life and wisdom of people in ancient times through fun activities and exhibits. There is a reproduction of an ancient Korean house from the Goguryeo era and even a reproduction of a pottery workshop and kiln on display. Additionally, children can even try on historical clothing, accessories, and golden crowns.    The museum exhibits reproductions of artifacts that are on display in the National Museum of Korea. Children will be able to learn and gain a deeper understanding of Korean cultural heritage through fun, hands-on experiences.','-10997','Daily 10:00 - 18:00 (KST)\n* Limited extended hours (Last Wednesday of every month)','Closed New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year & Chuseok','04383  137, Seobinggo-ro, Yongsan-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4 / Gyeongui Central Line  Ichon Station  Exit 2,  309m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=51803&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=51805&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=51807&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.526861,'ENP020547'),
(167,'Tteok Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/The-Tteok-Rice-Cake-Museum/ENP002037','The Tteok Museum is a museum and experience center where visitors can learn about traditional Korean food. Permanent Exhibition Hall No. 1 showcases the different tteok (rice cakes) that were prepared and eaten on Korean holidays. Also on display are the various tools that were needed to create the tteok. Permanent Exhibition Hall No. 2 has displays on the tteok that were eaten during the daily life of a Korean person. From birth, to death, and all the occasions in between, the tteok that were or are served are on display at the Tteok Museum. The museum also offers classes on how to make tteok and other traditional Korean food.','-6108','Daily 10:00 - 18:00','Closed Sundays, Lunar New Year, Chuseok','110-360  71, Donhwamun-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 1/3/5  Jongno 3(sam)-ga Station  Exit 7,  286m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14336&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14337&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14338&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=14339&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.574892,'ENP002037'),
