(173,'Seoul Art Space - Sindang Creative Arcade','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Sindang-Creative-Arcade/ENP005060','The Sindang Creative Arcade is a creative space for artists and an art market. The arcade was re-born into a space for the arts following renovation of empty storefronts at the Sindang Underground Shopping Center in the Jungang Market. The Jungang Market was established in 1917 and the renovation that created the Sindang Creative Arcade has revitalized the area. The creative arcade houses workshops and an art market. Dozens of artists create artworks and crafts in nearly every art medium there is. At the art market, shoppers can purchase unique artwork and items.','-10985','Artist Workshop 09:00 - 20:00 \nCommon Workshop & Photography Room 09:00 - 22:00','Art Market closed weekends','04571  87, Majang-ro, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 2/6  Sindang Station  Exits 2,  336m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23374&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23375&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23376&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23377&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.568961,'ENP005060'),
(174,'National Museum of Korean Contemporary History','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Museum-of-Contemporary-History/ENP006667','The National Museum of Korean Contemporary History houses exhibitions that span modern Korean history, from the first opening of Korea to outsiders in the late 19th century to today. The museum is the country\'s first national museum of contemporary history. The eight-story museum has many facilities: there are four permanent exhibition halls and two special exhibition halls, seminar rooms, lecture halls, a rooftop garden, a museum shop (that sells souvenirs), a cafe, and storage lockers. The four permanent exhibitions cover different periods of Korean history and there are over 1,500 artifacts and items here. Some of the displays are patriot Ahn Jung-Geun\'s last writings, the March 1st Declaration of Independence, belongings of fallen soldiers from the Korean War, and materials relating to democratic activism. The museum\'s first floor contains two special exhibition halls. Here, you will find a variety of limited-time exhibitions relating to Korean history, politics, society, and culture. Additionally, visitors can listen to, watch, and experience the modernization of Korea through state-of-the-art technology. There is also the Children\'s Museum, where children can learn and experience history for themselves with the museum??s ??Our History??s Treasure Chest??area.','-12823','10:00 - 18:00 (Wednesdays and Saturdays: 10:00 - 21:00) \n*Last entry 30 minutes before closing','Closed on New Year\'s Day & Chuseok','03141  198, Sejong-daero, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 5  Gwanghwamun Station  Exit 2,  217m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=41550&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=41549&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=41548&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=4&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72592&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72593&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.574003,'ENP006667'),
(175,'Nature Poem','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Nature-Poem-EN/ENP001439','Nature Poem is a six-story commercial gallery located in the heart of Gangnam\'s posh Cheongdam-dong neighborhood. Cheongdam-dong is famous for its abundance of premium designer stores. Nature Poem is located near many art galleries and high-end luxury stores, making a visit to Nature Poem a convenient starting point for a tour of Gangnam. Gallery GO, the Nam June Paik Museum and Gallery Jang are all nearby.','','Daily 10:00 - 18:00','Closed Sundays','06011  461, Apgujeong-ro, Gangnam-gu, Seoul','* Bundang Line, Apgujeong Rodeo Station, Exit 2 (10 mins on foot)* Subway Line 7, Cheongdam Station, Exit 9 (20 mins on foot)','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16665&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16666&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16667&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16668&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.526576,'ENP001439'),
(176,'National Meteorological Museum of Korea','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/National-Meteorological-Museum-of-Korea-EN/ENP040770','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}It is the first meteorological science and history museum that researches and preserves the meteorological culture of Korea from the Joseon Dynasty to modern times. The museum owns the world\'s last surviving rain gauge instrument, known as the Rain Gauge of the Chungcheonggamyeong Provincial Office, Gongju, invented 200 years earlier than the West.The Seoul Meteorological Observatory (52 Songwol-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul), where the National Meteorological Museum was established, is the center of Korea\'s modern and contemporary meteorological history. The modern meteorological observation started in Wonnam-dong, Gyeongseong, in 1907 and moved to Songwol-dong via Nakwon-dong. The building at the time of its establishment in 1932 and extension in 1939 have been maintained and served as the Korea Meteorological Administration until the administration moved to Dongjak-gu, Seoul, in 1998. For this continuity, it was selected as a ??00-year observatory??by the World Meteorological Organization in 2017. In 2016, when the museum was being built, the Seoul Meteorological Observatory was restored to its original form based on the architectural drawings of the 20th-century meteorological station kept at the National Archives. Please enjoy the change of weather and history at the National Meteorological Museum, the heart of Korea\'s meteorology.','-2994','10:00  - 18:00','Mondays, January 1, Lunar New Year??s Day and Chuseok','03178  52, Songwol-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 5  Seodaemun Station  Exit 4,  860m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=50900&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=50902&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=50904&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=50908&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.570748,'ENP040770'),
(177,'Jong Ie Nara Paper Art Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Jong-Ie-Nara-Paper-Art-Museum/ENP005796','The Jongienara Museum opened in 1999 as a Paper Art Museum and was established to revive and recreate Korea\'s world-class paper, K origami, and paper culture. Reopened as the Jongienara Museum in 2008, it goes beyond researching and introducing Korea\'s outstanding origami and paper culture. It pays attention to the excellent role of paper as a craft and art object, presenting the development of a new cultural art genre and modern paper culture and art. The excellence and creativity of Korean origami and paper culture are known to the public through the discovery, exhibitions, and education of current cultural paper artworks.','-10100','Daily 09:30 - 18:00 \n(Last entry 30 mins prior to close)','Closed Sundays & Holidays','100-391  166, Jangchungdan-ro, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3, Dongguk Univ. Station, Exit 3,  55m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=57693&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=57692&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=57691&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.559679,'ENP005796'),
(178,'Sungshin Women\'s University Costume Museum and Natural History Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Sungshin-Womens-University-Costume-Museum-and-Natural-History-Museum/ENP033828','p{text-align:justify;word-spacing:2px;}Opened on November 23, 2011, the Park Kwang Hoon Costume Museum is a special museum, displaying over 600 garments, which are currently designated as Seoul\'s Intangible Cultural Property No. 11, donated by the Master Artisan of Needlework, Park Kwang Hoon, as well as more than 2,000 pieces of fabrics and accessories. A variety of Korean attires and accessories are on display, from swaddling clothes and ordinary clothes as well as wedding clothes and royal ritual clothes to shrouds for the deceased.Located in the basement (B1) of the same building, the Natural History Museum exhibits as many as 135,000 samples collected for over 40 years since the 1970s under four themes of rocks, embryogenesis, plants and insects to help visitors learn and feel the nature around them.??Park Kwang Hoon Costume Museum offers various arts and culture programs, including the traditional pattern gilt stamping class, traditional pattern drawing class, and jokduri making class, in addition to its main exhibitions. ??Extra charges apply for experience programs.','CostumeMuseum:+82-2-920-2657NaturalHistoryMuseum:+','Mon - Sat 10:00 - 17:00 (Closed Sundays and Legal Holidays)','','01133  55, Dobong-ro 76ga-gil, Gangbuk-gu, Seoul  (Woonjung Green Campus, B1)','Subway Line 4  Mia Station  Exit 1,  500m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28635&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28636&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28637&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28638&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28639&fileTy=MEDI',6.000000,37.631950,'ENP033828'),
(179,'Culture Station Seoul 284','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Culture-Station-Seoul-284/ENP000450','Culture Station Seoul 284 is a multipurpose arts and cultural complex. It was once known simply as Seoul Station and it was the city\'s biggest rail station. The station was built during the Japanese colonial era. The first floor is used as a space for performances and exhibitions. The second floor is used for exhibitions, seminars, and meetings. Though admission to Culture Station Seoul 284 is free, performances and exhibitions may charge admission.','-6827','','','04509  1, Tongil-ro, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1/4/Airport Railroad/Gyeongui-Jungang Line/GTX-A  Seoul Station Exit 1,  76m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68381&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68382&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68383&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72582&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72583&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.557522,'ENP000450'),
(180,'Arko Art Center','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Arko-Art-Center/ENP018992','Arko Art Center is a public art gallery and art center in the Daehak-ro area. By curating temporary exhibitions, and creating a platform for emerging experimental artists, the gallery has successfully become a staple of the Korean contemporary art scene. The Arko Art Center is also home to INSA Art Space, an alternative space aimed at promoting upcoming artists, as well as maintaining archives and providing seminar rooms and project space. There is no admission fee for the center, but exhibitions may charge entry fees.','+82-2-760-4850ext.3','Daily 11:00 KST - 19:00 KST (Last entry at 18:30 KST)','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year, Chuseok & Christmas','03087  3, Dongsung-gil, Jongno-Gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Hyehwa Station  Exit 2,  138m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=11947&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73971&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73972&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=11948&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=11949&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.578828,'ENP018992'),
(181,'The Hangsangsoo Embroidery','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Hansangoo-Embroidery-Museum/ENP003357','This unique space preserves all the traces of traditional Korean embroidery techniques that have been restored by collecting and analyzing artifacts from the 1960s to revive Korean embroidery, which was lost through the Korean Empire and Japanese occupation. The Korean Handicraft Institute, which opened in 1963, is the origin of the Hansangsu Embroidery Museum. It has been established as a complex cultural space to preserve and present Korean embroidery to the public. The eldest daughter of Han Sang-soo, a National Intangible Cultural Property embroiderer, has been running the museum as the second director and is preparing for the third succession.','-3334','Tuesday-Sunday 10:00~18:00\nBreak Time 12:00~13:00','Monday','02836  4-10 Seongbuk-ro, Seongbuk-gu, Seoul','Subway  Line 4  Hansung University Station  Exit 5,  719m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60044&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60043&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60042&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60041&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60040&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.595526,'ENP003357'),
(182,'Leeum Museum of Art','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Leeum-Samsung-Museum-of-Art/ENP001232','The Leeum Museum of Art is the perfect place to enjoy traditional and contemporary art created by Korean and international artists. Most of the exhibits on display at the museum are based on the large collection of the founder, the late Lee Byeong-cheol, once president of the Samsung Group. Three world-renowned architects, Maria Botta, Jean Nouvel, and Rem Koolhaas, were commissioned to design the outstanding museum complex. The name Leeum is the acronym of the family name of its founder, ??Lee??and an abbreviated word for museum, ??um?? The museum is composed of three individual buildings linked together as a composite complex. Museum 1 showcases traditional Korean arts and crafts such as calligraphy, ceramic arts and metal craft work, while Museum 2 displays dynamic modern and contemporary art by domestic and international artists, this section includes the Samsung Child Education & Cultural Center which offers cultural education for children.  In the museum basement, a sunken garden and Gabion wall, which is a cylindrical metal container filled with stones, can be found. Art, architecture and nature exist together in perfect harmony.           Frequently Asked Questions about Leeum Museum of Art         Do I need to make a reservation to visit the Leeum Museum of Art?         Leeum Museum of Art operates under a reservation system. Reservations can be made 14 days before the visit. The maximum number of people per reservation is four. On-site ticketing is possible and limited to remaining tickets per reservation time (As of 2025)          Is the Leeum Museum of Art digital guide available for free?         Digital guides that automatically provide explanations when one approaches the exhibits can be borrowed free of charge. The devices are available to elementary school students and anyone older. You must present an identification card such as a passport or resident registration card. The digital guide is available in Korean, English, Chinese, and Japanese. (As of 2025)          Can I visit the Leeum Museum of Art permanent exhibitions for free?         Yes. Permanent exhibitions are free. They are also operated under a reservation system, so please make a reservation before visiting. (As of 2025)     { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@graph\": [{ \"@type\": \"FAQPage\", \"mainEntity\": [{ \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Do I need to make a reservation to visit the Leeum Museum of Art?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div>            Leeum Museum of Art operates under a reservation system. Reservations can be made 14 days before the visit. The maximum number of people per reservation is four. On-site ticketing is possible and limited to remaining tickets per reservation time (As of 2024)          </div>\" } }, { \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Is the Leeum Museum of Art digital guide available for free?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div>            Digital guides that automatically provide explanations when one approaches the exhibits can be borrowed free of charge. The devices are available to elementary school students and anyone older. You must present an identification card such as a passport or resident registration card. The digital guide is available in Korean, English, Chinese, and Japanese. (As of 2024)            </div>\" } }, { \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"Can I visit the Leeum Museum of Art permanent exhibitions for free?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": { \"@type\": \"Answer\", \"text\": \"<div>            Yes. Permanent exhibitions are free. They are also operated under a reservation system, so please make a reservation before visiting. (As of 2024)          </div>\" } }] }, { \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"Leeum Museum of Art\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"4.5\", \"ratin