(183,'Electricity Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Electricity-Museum/ENP001958','The Electricity Museum is an educational museum located within the KEPCO Art Center. Visitors can learn about the history of electricity here through fun activities, photos, models, and illustrations.','-10215','Daily 10:00 - 18:00','Closed Mondays, Lunar New Year & Chuseok','06732  60, Hyoryeong-ro 72-gil, Seocho-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3 & Shinbundang Line, Yangjae Station, Exit 1 (20 mins on foot)','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12429&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12430&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12431&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.485699,'ENP001958'),
(184,'Appenzeller Noble Memorial Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Appenzeller-Noble-Memorial-Museum/ENP006430','Learn about the history of education in Korea at the Appenzeller Noble Memorial Museum. The museum is housed in what was once the Pai Chai Hakdang, which was Korea\'s first Western-style school. Currently, the school\'s classrooms have been repurposed and are used as a permanent exhibition hall, a special exhibition hall, an experience zone, and a seminar room. In the permanent exhibition hall, visitors can see what the Pai Chai Hakdang looked like in the 1930s at the hall\'s recreated historical classroom. Admission to the museum is free.','-5817','Daily 10:00 - 17:00','Closed Mondays, Sundays & Public Holidays','04516  19, Seosomun-ro 11-gil, Jung-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1 / 2  City Hall Station  Exit 10,  240m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=31412&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=31413&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=31411&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=31410&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.563705,'ENP006430'),
(185,'National Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art, Seoul','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/National-Museum-of-Modern-and-Contemporary-Art-Seoul/ENP011658','The National Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art (MMCA), Seoul is the newest of the four branches. The Seoul branch focuses on introducing global contemporary art. Equipped with multiple facilities, including a library, theater, and a multipurpose hall, MMCA, Seoul strives to accommodate every mode of new artistic endeavors and communication with the public.','-13121','Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays, Fridays, and Sundays 10:00 - 18:00 (KST)\nWednesdays & Saturdays 10:00 - 21:00 (KST)\n* Special Night Exhibition 18:00 - 21:00 (KST)\n* Last Entry: 1 Hour Before Closing Time','New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year\'s Day & Chuseok','30, Samcheong-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 1,  764m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12792&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12793&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12794&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=12795&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74386&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.579512,'ENP011658'),
(186,'National Aviation Museum of Korea','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/National-Aviation-Museum-of-Korea/ENP038021','The National Aviation Museum of Korea, located at Gimpo Airport, is the first national museum in the aviation field established by the Ministry of Land, Infrastructure and Transport to organize Korea\'s aviation history and promote collective understanding of the aviation industry. The National Aviation Museum of Korea consists of the Aviation History Hall, where visitors can learn about the history of Korean aviation, the Aviation Industry Hall, where visitors can get a glimpse of the current state of the aviation industry, and the Aviation Future Hall, where visitors can see various aviation technologies, airplanes and models for the future. Additionally, there is a unique experience space for those who have always dreamed of flying. Here, visitors can experience aviation through five different spaces including the Black Eagle boarding experience, an in-flight training experience, a pilot control experience, the air sports experience, and the children\'s airport experience.    { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\", \"name\": \"National Aviation Museum of Korea\", \"aggregateRating\": { \"@type\": \"AggregateRating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5.0\", \"ratingCount\": \"1\" }, \"review\": [{ \"@type\": \"Review\", \"reviewRating\": { \"@type\": \"Rating\", \"ratingValue\": \"5\" }, \"author\": { \"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"traveller_12_14\" }, \"reviewBody\": \"From the very early days of mankind dreaming of flying, via Korea??s specific footprint in aviation up to the latest technological developments, the museum has compiled a really amazing and well guided exhibition.\", \"datePublished\": \"2023-05-02\" }] }','-10058','Daily 10:00 - 18:00','Closed Mondays\nJanuary 1, Lunar New Year??s Day\n*If Monday is a public holiday, the museum will be open on that Monday and closed on Tuesday.*','07505  177 Haneul-gil, Gangseo-gu, Seoul  (Gonghang-dong, National Aviation Museum of Korea)','Subway Line 5/9/Airport Railroad/Seohae Line/Gimpo Gold Line  Gimpo Airport Station Exit 4,  988m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42438&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42439&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42440&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42441&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42442&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.556756,'ENP038021'),
(187,'Hangaram Art Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Hangaram-Art-Museum/ENP004325','Hangaram Art Museum is situated on the left side of the main front area of the Seoul Arts Center. It is integrated with various programs offered by the Seoul Arts Center. The museum includes exhibition halls, storage rooms, and an art shop, providing an optimal exhibition environment. It often hosts special exhibitions by world-renowned artists such as Edvard Munch, Bernard Buffet, and Pablo Picasso. Most exhibitions prohibit photography, and observing proper viewing etiquette is important. The outdoor stair plaza serves as an open space for art markets, outdoor festivals, and an outdoor café during the summer season. It also accommodates various public programs, offering a unique cultural experience.','1668-1352','10:00 - 19:00 (KST)','Closed Mondays','06757  2406, Nambusunhwan-ro, Seocho-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Nambu Bus Terminal Station (Seoul Arts Center)  Exit 5,  695m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16910&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16911&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16912&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16913&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74167&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.478482,'ENP004325'),
(188,'Seoul Book Bogo','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seoul-Book-Bogo/ENP030789','p{text-align:justify;word-spacing:2px;}Seoul Book Bogo is a new cultural space created by Seoul Metropolitan Government to house old, secondhand books they gathered from old bookstores around the city. Featuring an old secondhand bookstore, library, and cultural programs, Seoul Book Bogo is separated into 4 spaces for value, sharing, enjoyment, and experience. Visitors can feel the value of old books in the space for value, read books donated by famous intellectuals in the space for sharing, experience unique indie books in the space for enjoyment, and participate in various cultural book programs in the space for experience.','-11850','Weekdays 11:00 AM - 9:00 PM\nSaturdays 10:00 AM - 9:00 PM\nSundays 10:00 AM - 6:00 PM','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year & Chuseok','05507  1, Ogeum-ro, Songpa-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 2, Jamsillaru Station, Exit 1,  160m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23411&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23413&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23414&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23412&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.521267,'ENP030789'),
(189,'Samseyoung','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/2024-samsy/ENPzcpf02','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}Samseyoung aims to be a cultural and artistic space that embraces the past, present, and future. Opened in December 2021, Samseyoung reflects on the past through the collection of antique art that the founder has gathered over 20 years. It is also a space where contemporary cultural and artistic figures come together to engage with the present while looking forward to the future.','-644','11:00-18:00','Sun-Mon','03003  2 Pyeongchang 44-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul  Samseyoung','Subway Line 3  Gyeongbokgung Station  Exit 3,  Take Bus 1711 and get off at Pyeongchang-dong Samsung Apartments. 301 m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68330&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68331&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68332&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68333&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68334&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.613679,'ENPzcpf02'),
(190,'Space C','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Space-C/ENP001441','Space C is a venue created and run by Coreana, a Korean cosmetics company. It spans 10 levels comprising a museum, gallery, beauty shop, café, and rooftop garden. On the 5th and 6th floors, visitors will find Korea??s largest cosmetics museum where visitors can learn about the history and development of Korean cosmetics. Space C also houses a large number of cosmetics-related artworks and other artifacts.      The Cosmetics Museum is Space C??s main exhibition hall, presenting the history of Korean cosmetics through a collection of more than 5,300 beauty-related items used by women in the Joseon Dynasty (1392-1910). The C Gallery on the first basement level is a traditional exhibition hall that displays fine art while C Cube on the second basement level plays host to more experimental work. The museum café on the 1st floor reflects the nature of its setting with art exhibits created from everyday objects, giving visitors the chance to continue their cultural odyssey even as they relax. The Beauty Space on the 2nd to 4th floors is a peaceful haven where women can consult a beauty therapist in the skin clinic and indulge in a range of body treatments. The Outdoor Cosmetics Museum on the rooftop of Space C is a garden featuring a collection of important plants which provide key ingredients for the cosmetics industry. From here, visitors can also enjoy spectacular views of the Seoul skyline.','-9644','Tuesday - Friday - 11:00 AM - 6:00 PM','Saturday,Sunday, Monday, January 1, Lunar New Year & Chuseok holidays\n* Please refer to the website as opening hours may vary.','06024  827, Eonju-ro, Gangnam-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3, Apgujeong Station, Exit 3,  567m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=804&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=805&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=806&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72449&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72450&fileTy=MEDIA&file',5.000000,37.523199,'ENP001441'),
(191,'Art Sonje Center','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Art-Sonje-Center/ENP002405','Whereas the Sonje Museum of Art typically focuses exclusively on contemporary artwork, the Art Sonje Center has a multi-pronged focus on art. The museum exhibits art from various genres and the museum also hosts cultural events such as concerts, short film screenings, and performance arts shows by Korean and foreign artists. Major pieces in the museum\'s collection are  Wings of Jupiter by Kwak Hoon and Curtains by Hwang Kyu-Baik.','-9602','Daily 12:00 - 19:00 (KST)','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year\'s Day & Chuseok','03062  87, Yulgok-ro 3-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 1,  709m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=38265&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74121&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',2.000000,37.579422,'ENP002405'),
(192,'Seoul Science Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/SeoulScienceMuseum/ENPn1ua1r','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}The Seoul Science Museum, located in Hageo-dong, Nowon-gu, opened its doors for the first time in Seoul in 2017. It was established to enhance science and cultural facilities in the Gangbuk area, aiming to bridge the gap in science and culture among different regions and promote balanced development across Seoul\'s districts. As a science experiential facility aimed at youth, it operates six permanent exhibition halls with 221 exhibits and a special rotating exhibition hall featuring exhibits related to the history of objects. It offers various educational programs and events, including family-friendly science-making experiences, group science classes for elementary, middle, and high school students, expert lectures, science experiments, and nature ecology programs that families can enjoy together.','-5390','Tue-Fri 09:30-17:30 KST','Closed every Monday, January 1st, and the day of Lunar New Year and Chuseok','01792  160, Hangeulbiseok-ro, Nowon-gu, Seoul','Subway Subway  Line1  Hagye Station  Exit 2,  1km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=61371&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=