(193,'Kumho Museum of Art','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Kumho-Museum-of-Art/ENP003100','The Kumho Museum of Art showcases artwork from famous, established artists as well as works from outstanding new artists. The museum hosts a concert series in their recital hall called the Kumho Gallery Concert. The concerts take place every Tuesday, Thursday, and Friday at 20:00 in the evening. There are also presentations on the artists and artworks on exhibition at the museum. These sessions are opened to the public as part of the museum\'s Kumho Academy. The Kumho Museum of Art is located near Gyeongbokgung Palace.','-5754','Daily 10:00 - 18:00 (KST) (Last entry at 17:30)','Closed Mondays, Lunar New Year\'s Day & Chuseok','110-061  18, Samcheong-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 1,  620m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16134&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16135&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16136&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=16137&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.577470,'ENP003100'),
(194,'The War Memorial of Korea','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/WarMemorialofKorea/ENP000859','The War Memorial of Korea was established to remember the Korean War (6. 25. 1950 - 7. 27.1953) and to symbolize the desire for peaceful reunification of Korea. The museum consists of 6 individual exhibition halls and a combat experience room, a screening room and an outdoor exhibition area with memorial statues.    The Statue of Brothers located in the south-west corner of the outdoor exhibition area at the museum symbolizes the Korean War and the hope for reunification. The statue depicts a scene where a family??s oldest son, a South Korean soldier and his younger brother, a North Korean soldier meet on a battlefield. Their embrace expresses reconciliation, love and forgiveness.   There is also an extensive garden area around the memorial with an artificial waterfall, and a lake where visitors can picnic whilst enjoying the beautiful landscape. The museum houses more than 10,000 artifacts in the indoor and outdoor exhibition areas. It takes visitors about three hours to complete the tour. The first floor exhibition hall features a history of war from prehistoric times up to the Korean War. The combat experience room on the third floor offers visitors a special opportunity to experience a simulated life and death situation on the battlefield through special effects.','-3743','Tue-Sun 09:30 - 18:00 \n*For more details, please refer to our website.','Closed Mondays & the day following national holidays','04353  29, Itaewon-ro, Yongsan-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 4  Samgakji Station  Exits 11,  227m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49153&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49154&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49155&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49156&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49157&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.539619,'ENP000859'),
(195,'Seoul Urban Life Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seoul-Urban-Life-Museum/ENP038243','The Seoul Urban Life Museum is a modern life and history museum that focuses on exhibitions and programs that allow guests to reminisce and interact with the memories of Seoul\'s citizens. There are facilities for everyone to enjoy, such as the Living Seoul Exhibition Room, which features displays on the life and scenery of Seoul, the Children\'s Experience Room for kids and the Special Exhibition room where various exhibitions are held throughout the year.','-6219','Daily 09:00 - 18:00 *Closed Mondays* (KST)','monday','01849  27, Dongil-ro 174-gil, Nowon-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 6 / 7  Taereung Station  Exit 5,  320m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42817&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42818&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42819&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=42820&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73895&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.619612,'ENP038243'),
(196,'Songeun Art Cube','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Songeun-Art-Cube/ENP003778','Songeun Art Cube (formerly known as Songeun Gallery) is a space for new artists to exhibit their artworks. Operated by the Songeun Art Foundation, the space functions as a gallery but various arts events also take place here. Ever since it opened in 2002, Songeun Art Cube has held an annual arts award ceremony. Winners are sponsored by the foundation and receive support to exhibit their work.','-3468','Daily 11:00 - 18:30','Closed Sundays & holidays','06182  441, Dosan-daero, Gangnam-gu, Seoul','Subway Suin Bundang Line  Apgujeong Rodeo Station  Exit 4,  637m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=50321&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=50322&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=50323&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=50324&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=50325&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.524175,'ENP003778'),
(197,'The Seoul Museum of History','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/The-Seoul-Museum-of-History/ENP002722','The Seoul Museum of History is the only museum in Korea that represents the city??s history and culture. Since its establishment on the former site of Gyeonghuigung Palace in 2002, the museum has offered visitors the chance to experience 600 years of Seoul??shistoryand culture through interactive exhibitions. The three-story museum is divided thematically into three exhibition areas, including a special exhibition area, a permanent exhibition area and a hall that exhibits collections donated by the public.      The museum offers accessible and interactive exhibitions to the public with various hands-on programs. For example, visitors are allowed to touch and explore the exhibits on display, which are replicas of originals in the museum. In addition, the museumoffersthe U-Exhibit Guidance System, an automatic translator (various languages are available) for visitors, which makes every tour convenient and interesting.','-918','KST 09:00 - 18:00 (Last Entry: 17:30 )\nExtended Hours: Every Friday until 21:00 \n*For more details, please visit the website.','Closed Mondays & New Year\'s Day','03177  55, Saemunan-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 5  Gwanghwamun Station  Exit 7,  462m\nSubway Line 5  Seodaemun Station  Exit 4,  641m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68733&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68734&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68735&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68736&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=68737&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.571466,'ENP002722'),
(198,'Maehun Yun Bong-Gil Memorial Hall','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Maehun-Yun-Bong-Gil-Memorial-Hall/ENP003759','The Maehun Yun Bong-Gil Memorial Hall is dedicated to the resistance fighter, Patriot Yun Bong-gil. Yun\'s pen name was Maehun and he was active in the Korean independence movement during the Japanese colonial era. Located in Seoul\'s Yangjae dong, the first floor of the memorial is an exhibition hall that displays relics and biographical information about Yun Bong-gil in chronological order. On the second floor, the exhibition hall contains photographs and other materials of the Korean independence movement organized by theme. Admission to the memorial hall is free.','-3886','* April to October: 10:00 - 18:00\n* November to March: 10:00 - 17:00\n??Last entry is 30 mins prior to closing','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year??s Day & Chuseok','06773   99, Maeheon-ro, Seocho-gu, Seoul','Subway Sinbundang Line  Yangjae Citizen\'s Forest Station  Exit 5,  179m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=2255&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=2257&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=2258&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74827&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=74828&fileTy=MEDIA&f',5.000000,37.470220,'ENP003759'),
(199,'The store from Tong-in','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Tong-in-Shop/ENP025931','The oldest gallery specializing in antique art in Insadong, it was founded in 1924 as an antique art store representing Korea and became the backbone of culture and art during the turbulent times. The Tongin Gallery is located inside the Tongin Store and has become the center of Insadong as a complex cultural art space where ancient and contemporary art coexist. It is famous for its ancient art representing Korea and is a favorite place for world leaders. The tiger from a familiar folk tale is the representative character of Tongin Gallery.','-5520','Tue-Sat 10:30~18:30, Sun 12:00~17:00 KST','Mondays','03148  32 Insadong-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1/3/5  Jongno 3-ga Station  Exit 5,  334m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60307&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60304&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60305&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60306&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=60308&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.573802,'ENP025931'),
(200,'Gongpyeong Historic Sites Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Gongpyeong-Historic-Sites-Museum/ENP026675','Gongpyeong Historic Sites Museum was created when well preserved 16th century Joseon sites were dug up during redevelopment phases of Gongpyeong district 1, 2, and 4.  The museum is largely divided into 4 parts: ??Coexistence of Development and Preservation?? ??Gyeonpyeong-bang of the Joseon Dynasty Period?? ??Modern Gongpyeong-dong?? and ??Historic Sites Archives.?? The completed Gongpyeong Historic Sites Museum displays the various relics and building structures of a neighborhood which managed to remain undisturbed for over 600 years, allowing visitors a closer look at the daily lives of people who had lived back in the Joseon Dynasty.','-779','Daily 09:00 - 18:00 (KST)','Closed Mondays','03161  26, Ujeongguk-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul  (B1, Centropolis)','Subway Line 1  Jonggak Station  Exit 3-1,  69m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20284&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20283&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20286&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20285&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20282&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.571616,'ENP026675'),
(201,'Platform-L Contemporary Art Center','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/PLATFORM-L/ENPn0wsm1','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}Platform-L Contemporary Art Center was established to provide audiences with diverse artistic experiences through the creative endeavors of contemporary artists and to contribute to a society enriched with imagination and inspiration. Since its opening in spring 2016, Platform-L has housed facilities including galleries, a live hall, an open courtyard, and lecture rooms. The center presents exhibitions, performances, and video works across a wide range of genres and media.','-11319','11:00-20:00','Closed every Monday','06053  11, Eonju-ro 133-gil, Gangnam-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 7, Hakdong Station, Exit 10, 284m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75518&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75519&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75520&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=75521&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&par