(202,'Mokin Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Mokin-Museum/ENP001809','The Mokin Museum specializes in traditional wooden sculptures and woodwork. The museum is located in Insa-dong and consists of an underground lounge, an exhibition hall, and a rooftop garden. The museum collection includes traditional Korean wooden sculptures as well as traditional masks, staffs and wooden dolls from other parts of Asia. Mokin hosts various exhibitions and events throughout the year.','-5697','* Summer Season 10:30 - 19:00 (Last entry at 18:00) \n* Winter Season 10:30 - 18:00 (Last entry at 17:00)','Closed Sundays, Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year & Chuseok','03022  46-1 Changuimun-ro 5-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Gyeongbokgung Station  Exit 2,  1.9km\nGet off at Buam-dong Community Center and walk 500m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17226&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17227&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17228&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17229&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73932&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.589007,'ENP001809'),
