(204,'Seo Gallery','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seo-Gallery/ENP001966','The Seo Gallery is an arts gallery in Banpo-dong, Seoul. Its exhibitions cover a wide variety of different mediums including, but not limited to, painting, sculpture, photography, architecture, design, and fashion. The gallery also provides various programs to support both older artists and to foster new artists.','-6115','10:00 - 17:00 (KST)','Closed Weekends','06648  94, Banpo-daero, Seocho-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 2, Seocho Station, Exit 2','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17252&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17253&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17254&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17255&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.489811,'ENP001966'),
(205,'Donuimun Museum Village','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Donuimun-Museum-Village/ENP023761','The Donuimun Museum Village is an outdoor village that consists of hanok (traditional Korean homes) and buildings that showcase historical eras of Seoul architecture. Visitors can see the architectural styles of the 1900s up to the 1980s at this special outdoor museum. Founded in September 2017, the museum village is conveniently located between the Gangbuk Samsung Hospital and the Seoul Museum of History.       Through urban regeneration efforts, Donuimun Museum Village has preserved 40 out of 63 houses in    Saemunan,    an old neighborhood district. Architecture from Korea\'s modern history era and Joseon Dynasty exist side by side in this newly developed cultural space.       The renovated houses were rehabilitated as exhibition and experience spaces.      ??An exhibition space where the history of Saemunan-dong and the sensibility of the analog generation are alive      - Donuimun Museum Village, Donuimun Club, Seoul Future Heritage Hall, 60s 80s emotional spaces (Citizens??Life History Hall, Saemunan Theater, Seodaemun Photo Studio, and more)       ??Learn about modern and contemporary culture and art in a calm hanok with ??Artist\'s time??(9 Hanok-dong locations)      - Various experience programs such as Socks Remnants Craft Workshop, Hanji (Korean Paper) Craft Workshop, Maedeup (Knot) Workshop, traditional mask clock making, and Danoseon making      - Donuimun Market, Donuimun Time Travel Club, Immersive Theater (??a hundred-year-old night??, Memories??Music Cafe (Saturdays 12:00-15:00), Donuimun Night School         Both interior and exterior including the alleyways, yards, and walls of the village are all part of this unique exhibition playground. Various performances and events including flea market and food trucks will take place in the village square and visitors are encouraged to walk around the village alleyways to learn more about Saemunan and its past residents.','-7653','Tue-Sun 10:00 - 19:00 (KST)','Closed Mondays & New Year\'s Day','03178  14-3, Songwol-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 5, Seodaemun Station, Exit 4, 349m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=71820&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=71821&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=71822&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=71823&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.570748,'ENP023761'),
(206,'THEO','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/2024-THEO/ENP9q04ig','.se-contents .se-scrollbox{overflow-x: auto; -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none;}.se-contents .se-scrollbox::-webkit-scrollbar{display: none;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image .se-caption{max-width: 100% !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video{max-width: 100%; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-image > img, .se-contents .se-responsive.se-video > *{max-width: 100%; min-width: 10px; height: auto !important;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper{position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; display: block;}.se-contents .se-responsive.se-video .se-video-wrapper > iframe{width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; position: absolute; left: 0px}Gallery THEO, known for showcasing Korean art\'s broad spectrum and diversity, was established in 2020 by two directors with experience in the UK and the international art market. They aimed to introduce global expertise and networks to the Korean art scene. Located in front of the UNESCO World Heritage site Seonjeongneung, THEO is dedicated to supporting young and talented Korean artists, regardless of artistic genre, and uncovering the potential in their works. The gallery actively provides a platform for Korean artists to grow and thrive. In addition, THEO introduces international artists to the Korean and Asian art communities, fostering cross-cultural exchanges and expanding artistic discourse beyond national borders. THEO continues to host exhibitions featuring diverse artists worldwide. It aims to create a space where artists can coexist and flourish, driven by a commitment to challenging projects and artistic excellence.','-7766','13:00~19:00','Monday, Sunday, and public holidays','06156  B1, 55-3 Bongeunsa-ro 68-gil, Gangnam-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 9  Samsung Jungang Station  Exit 6,  539m','https://english.visitseo