(208,'Seoul Sewerage Science Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Seoul-Sewerage-Science-Museum-1/ENP033825','p { text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; }  Established in 2017 to promote the history and science of sewerage, the Seoul Sewerage Science Museum is the nation\'s first science museum specializing in sewerage. It was constructed at the site of the Cheonggyecheon Sewage Treatment Plant, the country\'s first sewage disposal plant, to continue the historical significance and values of the facility. The museum is also a space that is centered on on-site experience, comprised of a science exhibition hall that displays the history, technology, and future of domestic and overseas sewerage, as well as a water reclamation center where visitors can take a look around sewerage facilities. As the center of environmental education, the Seoul Sewerage Science Museum offers various programs to teach the process of sewage purification and the significance of water.','-4671','Tue - Sun 09:00 ??17:00 (Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year\'s, and Chuseok)','','04809  64, Jadongchasijang 3-gil, Seongdong-gu, Seoul (Seoul Sewerage Science Museum)  250-4, Yongdap-dong','Subway Line 5  Janghanpyeong Station  Exit 8,  1.2km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28620&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28621&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28622&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28623&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=28624&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.557956,'ENP033825'),
(209,'Gallery Kong','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Gallery-Kong/ENP026676','Since its opening in 2005, Gallery Kong has showcased a wide range of globally famous photographers, greatly influencing the photography industry in Korea.    When the gallery moved into the newly built facility next to Cheongwadae??s Chunchugwan in Samcheong-dong, it expanded from being just a photo gallery to a multimedia gallery displaying all kinds of modern art, including communication arts, sculpture, video installations, etc.    By showcasing works of globally famous artists like Bernard Faucon (France), Chen Ruo Bing (China), Michael Kenna (UK), and Erwin Olaf (Netherlands), Gallery Kong is a gallery which shows the trend of contemporary art in 21st century Korea. This gallery also plays a very crucial role in helping Korean artists establish presence abroad by connecting them to galleries and shows outside Korea.','-8434','* Tuesdays - Saturdays 10:00 - 18:00','Closed Mondays, Sundays','03049  38, Samcheong-ro 7-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3, Anguk Station, Exit 1,  1.2 km\nSubway Line 3, Gyeongbokgung Station, Exit 5,  1.5 km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20287&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20288&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20289&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20290&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=20291&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.584028,'ENP026676'),
(210,'Hwanghakjeong Korean Archery Gallery','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Hwanghakjeong-Korean-Archery-Gallery/ENP029767','Hwanghakjeong Korean Archery Gallery is a place where visitors can go to learn about the history of archery in Korea and see the excellent quality of Korean bows. Made up of 5 different sections including exhibition halls, experience centers, and a permanent exhibition showcasing donated artifacts, this gallery is a great place for visitors to learn about traditional Korean archery and offers various programs where visitors can make arrows, try out archery, and more.','-2242','KST 10:00 - 17:00','Closed Monday, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year & Chuseok','03027  15-32 Sajik-ro 9-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul, Republic of Korea  Hwanghakjeong Archery Museum','Subway Line 3  Gyeongbokgung Station  Exit 1,  841m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22587&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22589&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22590&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22588&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',4.000000,37.577007,'ENP029767'),
(211,'Sungkok Art Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Sungkok-Art-Museum/ENP001907','p { text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; } The Sungkok Art Museum was established in 1995 to promote and foster Korean arts. The museum also commemorates the late founder of the Ssangyong Group, Kim Sungkok, and the museum was built on the site of Kim Sungkok\'s house. Creative work from all artistic genres such as photography, design, and fashion, is showcased in various exhibitions. The museum typically hosts more than a dozen exhibitions each year. There are three exhibition halls and an outdoor sculpture garden.','-8307','Daily 10:00 - 18:00 (KST)\n* Last entry at 17:30 (KST)','Closed Sundays, Mondays & Holidays','03175  42, Gyeonghuigung-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Gyeongbokgung Station  Exit 7,  611m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17256&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17257&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17258&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=17259&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73924&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.572277,'ENP001907'),
(212,'Donuimun Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Donuimun-Museum/ENP029381','p{ text-align:justify; word-spacing:2px; } Donuimun Museum is a new cultural space constructed from old restaurant buildings located in the old neighborhood of Saemunan. Originally built as residential homes back in 1960, these buildings were used as restaurants from 1990 to 2000, some of which included Italian restaurant AGIO and Korean restaurant Hanjeong. While preserving the architecture of the old structure, the buildings were reinforced for safety during their renovation into exhibition spaces.  Located in a central location within Saemunan surrounded by Seoul City Wall and the walls of Gyeonghuigung Palace, the spaces inhabited by AGIO and Hanjeong hold great historical and cultural value. When portions of Gyeonghuigung Palace Wall were discovered underground, the site has been transformed to preserve and display the remains. At Donuimun Museum, visitors can learn about the culture and history surrounding the area around it.     Donuimun Museum  AGIO     * History of the Donuimun Gate Area: After Ports Were Opened/History of the Donuimun Gate Area: Joseon Dynasty (1F)  * Records and Recollections of Two Villages : Gyonam-dong and Saemunan Village (2F)      Donuimun Museum  Hanjeong     * Urban Regeneration of the Saemunan Village / Photo Gallery (1F)  * The Story of Saemunan Village People (2F)      Donuimun Museum  Historic Remains     * Ruins of Gyeonghuigung Palace Wall        About the museum','-915','Daily 09:00 - 18:00 (KST) (Last admission 17:30)','Closed Mondays & New Year\'s Day','03178  35-54, Saemunan-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 5  Seodaemun Station  Exit 4,  400m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22214&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22215&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=22216&