(216,'KCDF Gallery','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/KCDFGallery/ENP037044','Located along the street of tradition itself, Insadong, KCDF Gallery is a space dedicated to the exhibition of crafts and was created to help promote the rise of the crafts industry, while contributing to a communicative platform for craftsmen and women, as well as the  dissessimation of the  consumer culture of crafts. The KCDF Library is also available, serving as a ground for  research activity that offers literature and various data on  a wide array of crafts designs along with  exhibitions, training programs, and  seminar spaces  for artists in the crafts design culture industry. On the first-floor shop of the gallery, visitors may also purchase premium crafts created by some of the finest specialists and artists in the country.* The Korea Craft & Design Foundation is a public government organization operated by the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism that was established for the promotion of crafts, public design, and traditional & lifestyle culture. The foundation focuses on establishing a cultural identify of Korea through the  dissessimation  and promotion of crafts, design, and tradtional & lifestyle cultures , in addition to contributing to an improved quality of life by strengthening the country\'s compeitive capactiy.','-10034','- Exhibition hall: Tue-Sun 10:00 - 18:00\n- Craft Garden: Tue-Sun 10:00 - 19:00\n(Break time 12:00 - 13:00)\n- KCDF Data Room: Tue-Fri 09:00 - 18:00 / Sat 10:00-19:00\n(Break time 12:00 - 13:00)','','03145  8, Insadong 11-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 6,  380m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40197&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40198&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=40199&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/co