(217,'The Museum of Korean Medical History','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Museum-of-Korean-Medical-History-at-Kyung-Hee-University/ENP006886','The Museum of Korean Medical History at Kyung Hee University displays a wealth of information relating to medicine and history. Some of the artifacts on display are ancient medical books, medical records, and artifacts relating to traditional Korean medicine. Visitors can also learn about the development of traditional medicine in Korea throughout history and information is displayed by time period. The museum is open to the public.','-4074','Daily 10:00 - 16:00','Closed Weekends & Holidays','130-050  26, Kyungheedae-ro, Dongdaemun-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 1  Hoegi Station  Exit 1,  1.2km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3764&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3765&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3766&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.596712,'ENP006886'),
(218,'Samsung Museum of Publishing','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Samsung-Museum-of-Publishing/ENP003330','p { text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; }  The Samsung Museum of Publishing is a private museum dedicated to all things related to printing and publishing. Located in Gugi-dong, Jongno-gu, visitors can see all manner of artifacts and historical items at the museum. Founded in 1990 by Kim Jonggyu of the Samsung Publishing Company, guided tours in Korean are available if reserved in advance.','-6858','Weekdays 10:00 - 17:00 (KST)','Closed weekends & holidays','03007  2-2, Bibong-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 3 & 6, Bulgwang Station, Exit 2\n(Take bus nos. 7022 or  7211 ??Get off at Gugi Tunnel stop)\n Subway Line 3, Gyeongbokgung Station, Exit 3\n(Take bus nos. 7022 or 7212 ??Get off at Gugi Tunnel stop)','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23378&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23379&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23380&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=23381&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73781&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.608704,'ENP003330'),
(219,'Kim Joong-up House of Architectural Culture','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Kim-Joong-up-House-of-Architectural-Culture/ENP042446','Built in the 1970s, this two-story detached house was remodeled in 1986 by Kim Joong-up, who added exotic elements to every corner of the house based on traditional Korean architecture. This is a place where you can get a glimpse of the housing culture of the middle class at the time, and was designated as a Seoul Future Heritage in 2017. The KimJoong-up House of Architectural Culture harmoniously integrates Korean and Western architectural styles. The second-floor living room has an umul-maru, rafter structure, and windows covered with changhoji paper, which are mainly used in hanok, but with a modern interpretation. In contrast, the bathroom was designed in a European style. The dry bathroom with a dressing room attached, something that wasn??t common in Korea during the \'70s and \'80s, has a vintage jade-colored interior that stands out. Stepping out to the elegantly decorated garden, a water element, a characteristic of Kim Joong-up\'s architecture, is located on one side of the yard. Even equipped with its own small greenhouse, the Kim Joong-up House of Architectural Culture contains immense nature in the garden.','-9962','Daily 10:00 ~ 17:00','Closed Sundays & Mondays','02755  11, Jangwi-ro 21na-gil, Seongbuk-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 6, Dolgoji Station, Exit 2,  1.5km','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56688&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56689&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56690&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56691&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=56692&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.614982,'ENP042446'),
(220,'The Story of King Sejong ??The Story of Admiral Yi Sunshin','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/King-Sejong-and-Admiral-Yi-Sunshin/ENP005465','The Story of King Sejong and The Story of Admiral Yi Sunshin are exhibitions halls about two of Korea\'s national heroes, King Sejong and Admiral Yi. The exhibition halls are located on the B2 level of the Sejong Center for the Performing Arts. In addition to viewing the exhibitions, children can also experience traditional Korean culture and try on hanbok. For more information on these activities, please ask at the information desk.','-1319','Daily 10:00 - 18:30 (Last entry at 18:00 ) *Closed Mondays*','','03172  175, Sejong-daero, Jongno-gu, Seoul','* Subway Line 3, Gyeongbokgung Station, Exit 6   * Subway Line 5, Gwanghwamun Station, Exit 2 (30 m on foot)* Subway Line 1, Jonggak Station, Exit 1','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3083&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3084&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3085&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L',3.000000,37.572722,'ENP005465'),
(221,'Lotte World Folk Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Lotte-World-Folk-Museum/ENP005815','The Lotte World Folk Museum highlights Korean folk culture through miniature displays. Located at Lotte World, visitors can enjoy seeing model villages from different periods of history. There is also a crafts room where visitors can see traditional crafts being made. The museum has a children\'s educational facility that runs various kid-friendly programs during school breaks.','+82-2-411-4761~5','* Weekdays: 11:00 - 19:00 KST\n* Weekends: 11:00 - 20:00 KST\n??Last entry is 1 hour before closing.','Open year round','05554  240, Olympic-ro, Songpa-gu, Seoul','Subway Lines 2 / 8, Jamsil Station, Exit 2, 144m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3255&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3256&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=3&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=3257&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73589&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=73590&fileTy=MEDIA&f',5.000000,37.511286,'ENP005815'),
(222,'Jeongdok Public Library','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Jeongdok-Public-Library/ENP001596','The Jeongdok Public Library was established to provide Seoulites and visitors with a space to study and enjoy books. The library is affiliated with Yanbian Library in the Yanbian Korean Autonomous Prefecture of China and Japan\'s Tokyo Metropolitan Library. The Jeongdok Public Library is one of the major libraries of the city\'s public library system.','-7730','Study Rooms\n* Weekdays 07:00 - 22:00 (November - February 08:00 - 22:00)\n* Weekends 07:00 - 22:00 (November - February 08:00 - 22:00)','Closed on the 1st & 3rd Wednesday of the month, national holidays, and other days as designated by the library','03055  48, Bukchon-ro 5-gil, Jongno-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 3  Anguk Station  Exit 2,  720m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49854&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49855&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49856&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49857&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=2&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=49858&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.580614,'ENP001596'),
(223,'Gyeomjae Jeong Seon Art Museum','https://english.visitseoul.net/attractions/Gyeomjae-Jeong-Seon-Art-Museum/ENP001961','The Gyeomjae Jeong Seon Art Museum is dedicated to the Joseon-era artist Jeong Seon. Located in Gangseo-gu, the museum has 4 levels. In addition to the special exhibition halls, there is a permanent memorial hall with information about the life and works of Jeong Seon. The museum\'s multipurpose facility can be used for lectures, seminars, and video screenings.','-4785','Tuesday to Friday: 10:00 ??18:00 \nSaturday and Sunday: 10:00 ??17:00 \nNational Holidays 10:00 - 17:00 \n??Last entry is 1 hour before closing.','Closed Mondays, New Year\'s Day, Lunar New Year\'s Day & Chuseok','07522  36, Yangcheon-ro 47-gil, Gangseo-gu, Seoul','Subway Line 9, Yangcheon Hyanggyo Station  Exit 1,  487m','https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72845&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72846&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72847&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72848&fileTy=MEDIA&fileNo=1&thumbTy=L | https://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&parentSn=72849&fileTy=MEDI',5.000000,37.572232,'ENP001961'),
